WEBVTT

00:10.370 --> 00:15.440
♪ no sanctuary
for your broken heart ♪

00:15.440 --> 00:17.380
♪ I left you standing there
in the dark... ♪

00:17.380 --> 00:19.150
Another one.

00:19.150 --> 00:20.180
Which one?

00:20.180 --> 00:21.180
The redhead
in the hoodie.

00:21.180 --> 00:22.750
She totally just
checked you out.

00:22.750 --> 00:24.420
-Yeah?
-Yeah!

00:24.420 --> 00:26.390
She probably thinks I'm on
the football team or something.

00:26.390 --> 00:27.790
Yeah. Probably.

00:27.790 --> 00:29.660
You know, I always wanted
to play college football.

00:29.660 --> 00:31.430
Well, you just
needed someone

00:31.430 --> 00:32.630
To believe in you.

00:32.630 --> 00:34.400
You needed a sar-bear.

00:34.400 --> 00:37.330
[both laughing]

00:37.330 --> 00:39.100
Sarah! Where have you been?

00:39.100 --> 00:41.100
Oh, my god.
That's my old roommate.

00:41.100 --> 00:42.540
Cheryl! Hi!

00:42.540 --> 00:44.270
Good to see you.

00:44.270 --> 00:45.540
Are you coming
back to school?

00:45.540 --> 00:46.640
I am, in the fall.

00:46.640 --> 00:48.180
In the meantime,

00:48.180 --> 00:49.540
I'm just working hard
and saving my pennies.

00:49.550 --> 00:51.150
What are you doing on campus?

00:51.150 --> 00:53.610
I'm just going to show rick
some of our old haunts.

00:53.620 --> 00:57.180
[rock music blasting,
boisterous chatter]

00:57.190 --> 00:59.290
[♪]

01:02.060 --> 01:03.760
Hello, boys.

01:03.760 --> 01:07.190
Hope we're not
interrupting your studies.

01:07.200 --> 01:10.430
[♪]

01:14.140 --> 01:16.270
Two bags.

01:18.440 --> 01:20.440
How's our inventory?

01:20.440 --> 01:22.080
[merchandise rustling]

01:22.080 --> 01:23.410
Getting low.

01:23.410 --> 01:25.280
Dime.

01:26.580 --> 01:28.450
Come here.

01:30.550 --> 01:31.820
We made more today

01:31.820 --> 01:33.290
Than you used to make
in a month.

01:33.290 --> 01:34.690
And once we expand
into other frats

01:34.690 --> 01:36.190
And all the other colleges
in the area--

01:36.190 --> 01:37.320
We'll be
rolling in it.

01:37.330 --> 01:38.630
People mess up
because they get greedy.

01:38.630 --> 01:39.730
You and I
are gonna be smart.

01:39.730 --> 01:41.730
We're gonna invest
in mutual funds.

01:41.730 --> 01:43.130
Ah, I like the way
your mind works.

01:43.130 --> 01:46.230
I love the way
your body works.

01:46.240 --> 01:48.270
[♪]

01:54.610 --> 01:56.440
Here?
Are you crazy?

01:56.450 --> 01:58.550
For you.

01:58.550 --> 02:01.350
[♪]

02:02.720 --> 02:03.750
Next fall,

02:03.750 --> 02:05.220
You'll be
back at purdue

02:05.220 --> 02:06.720
With all these
smart douche-bags.

02:06.720 --> 02:08.419
I don't want them.
I need you.

02:14.260 --> 02:17.300
You're my big, strong
papa bear.

02:17.300 --> 02:20.470
[♪]

02:26.710 --> 02:29.510
[♪]

02:33.820 --> 02:34.920
[engine rumbles off]

02:34.920 --> 02:37.480
[music blasting from house]

02:38.620 --> 02:39.790
Damn it, rick.

02:39.790 --> 02:40.920
I'll talk to him.

02:40.920 --> 02:42.260
I said they could
be here a few weeks.

02:42.260 --> 02:43.720
They've been here
four months.

02:43.730 --> 02:44.860
When are they going
back to vegas?

02:44.860 --> 02:46.390
I'll talk to him.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.460
I want them gone.

02:54.840 --> 02:57.800
[stereo blasting rock music]

02:57.810 --> 02:59.640
[♪]

03:03.880 --> 03:05.680
[turns music quiet]

03:05.680 --> 03:07.410
Dude?
I love that song.

03:07.420 --> 03:09.220
The neighbors
are gonna call the cops.

03:09.220 --> 03:11.820
The neighbors are customers.
They're not calling anybody.

03:11.820 --> 03:13.620
-What's with the coke?
-Business opportunity.

03:13.620 --> 03:16.520
The guy I buy from
sold it to me for three "g"s.

03:16.530 --> 03:17.860
Cut...

03:17.860 --> 03:19.630
It'll net 10.

03:19.630 --> 03:21.830
Hey! You guys
are finally back.

03:21.830 --> 03:24.430
Have a line.
Catch up with us, sar.

03:24.430 --> 03:26.800
You're so full of
crap, drew. Seven grand?

03:26.800 --> 03:28.440
How much have you
shoved up your nose?

03:28.440 --> 03:29.340
Eat me.

03:29.340 --> 03:30.240
In your dreams.

03:30.240 --> 03:31.940
Hey, somebody needs a drink

03:31.940 --> 03:34.310
And a hit and a line.

03:34.310 --> 03:35.640
Drew!

03:35.640 --> 03:36.840
What happened

03:36.850 --> 03:38.710
To the music, man?

03:38.710 --> 03:40.650
I want this crap
out of my house.

03:40.650 --> 03:42.920
Okay.
So help us get rid of it.

03:51.930 --> 03:54.800
[stereo and game console
both blasting]

03:54.800 --> 03:57.400
[♪]

04:02.900 --> 04:06.870
[♪]

04:15.720 --> 04:17.250
Hey!

04:17.250 --> 04:19.750
Come and dance
with us.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.890
Get off of me!

04:21.890 --> 04:23.890
Oh, god.
You're so boring.

04:23.890 --> 04:25.960
Forget it, trish.

04:25.960 --> 04:28.830
They'd rather
play with themselves.

04:28.830 --> 04:30.830
[women snickering]

04:30.830 --> 04:33.530
I'm gonna go
to bed soon.

04:33.540 --> 04:34.570
You wanna come
with me?

04:34.570 --> 04:35.570
In a bit.

04:35.570 --> 04:36.970
In a bit! Come on!

04:36.970 --> 04:40.640
It sucks being the only one
with a real job.

04:40.640 --> 04:43.280
[♪]

04:44.480 --> 04:46.350
[game blasting]

04:46.350 --> 04:48.380
Oh!

04:48.380 --> 04:50.980
[♪]

05:04.730 --> 05:06.700
Where is it, drew?

05:06.700 --> 05:07.670
Chill, sarah!

05:07.670 --> 05:08.740
Stay out of this, trish!

05:08.740 --> 05:09.970
What's going on?

05:09.970 --> 05:12.440
He stole my money!
My purdue money! $2,500!

05:12.440 --> 05:14.740
I borrowed it
to buy the coke.

05:14.740 --> 05:16.510
That was my tuition money,
you ass!

05:16.510 --> 05:19.310
Shut your bitch up, rick, before
I do.

05:19.320 --> 05:21.950
-I'm gonna kill that bitch!
-Stay down, drew!

05:21.950 --> 05:23.650
Stay down! Stay down!

05:23.650 --> 05:25.590
Outside. Outside!

05:26.590 --> 05:27.890
Hey. Hey!

05:27.890 --> 05:28.990
That money
is my everything!

05:28.990 --> 05:30.560
Rick,
it's my future.

05:30.560 --> 05:31.790
You said you'd
always protect me.

05:31.790 --> 05:32.760
Okay. Okay.
I'll handle it.

05:32.760 --> 05:36.460
You need to calm down.

05:36.470 --> 05:37.900
[panting]

05:37.900 --> 05:40.000
I'm gonna go
get some cigarettes.

05:40.000 --> 05:41.570
I'll be back
in 15 minutes.

05:41.570 --> 05:45.640
Okay. Okay.
Let papa bear handle this.

05:46.810 --> 05:49.710
[♪]

06:03.560 --> 06:05.590
[sighs]

06:09.630 --> 06:12.100
[tv plays quietly]

06:14.970 --> 06:17.600
Rick?

06:17.610 --> 06:20.070
Rick?

06:22.010 --> 06:25.010
[♪]

06:27.620 --> 06:29.450
[gasping]

06:32.620 --> 06:35.390
[breathing raggedly]

06:36.490 --> 06:37.890
[gasps and yelps]

06:37.890 --> 06:39.730
Rick!
What did you do?

06:39.730 --> 06:41.130
Drew went for the gun.

06:41.130 --> 06:43.730
I-it happened so fast.
He-- he was gonna kill me.

06:43.730 --> 06:45.170
Oh, my god.

06:45.170 --> 06:46.770
He took your money,
sarah, all right?

06:46.770 --> 06:48.030
I-I had to get it back.
I had to get your money back.

06:48.040 --> 06:49.540
He went for the gun!

06:49.540 --> 06:51.040
But what about trish?
Why did you shoot trish?

06:51.040 --> 06:52.170
She came at me!
I don't know!

06:52.170 --> 06:53.170
It just happened so fast!

06:53.180 --> 06:54.780
Did you call the cops?

06:54.780 --> 06:56.480
No, no, no. They'll never
believe a guy with my record.

06:56.480 --> 06:57.610
I've already got
two strikes against me.

06:57.610 --> 06:58.910
This is self-defense,
though, right?

06:58.910 --> 07:00.510
It doesn't matter.

07:00.520 --> 07:01.720
Okay, all right,

07:01.720 --> 07:03.020
I-I-it's just like
you always said, right?

07:03.020 --> 07:04.680
We need a plan,
so, we'll, you know,

07:04.690 --> 07:06.490
We'll, uh...
We'll get rid of the bodies,

07:06.490 --> 07:07.790
And we'll clean up the mess,

07:07.790 --> 07:11.460
And we'll go away
till this all blows over.

07:11.460 --> 07:12.690
Go get the blankets
from the bedroom.

07:12.690 --> 07:14.660
I can't, rick, I can't.

07:14.660 --> 07:17.130
Damn it, sarah, go!
We have to move!

07:18.870 --> 07:21.600
[♪]

07:21.600 --> 07:24.140
[corpse thudding]

07:25.770 --> 07:28.510
[♪]

07:39.820 --> 07:41.520
[lid clattering]

07:41.520 --> 07:42.660
[slam]

07:42.660 --> 07:45.030
[♪]

07:52.870 --> 07:55.500
[gasps and vomits]

07:55.500 --> 07:56.800
[sobbing]

07:57.870 --> 08:00.240
[rick]: Go to work.
You gotta act normal.

08:00.240 --> 08:02.640
Nothing's ever
gonna be normal again.

08:07.050 --> 08:09.020
I'd die for you, sarah.

08:09.020 --> 08:12.050
I won't let anything
happen to you.

08:18.130 --> 08:22.130
[indistinct announcement
crackling over p.A.]

08:30.710 --> 08:32.610
[♪]

08:32.610 --> 08:34.010
[reporter]:
Early this morning,

08:34.010 --> 08:36.710
Both shot to death
and wrapped in blankets,

08:36.710 --> 08:39.110
We found inside
a trash dumpster

08:39.110 --> 08:40.750
Behind the local...

08:40.750 --> 08:42.280
[announcement
becomes distorted]

08:42.280 --> 08:44.280
The woman, who authorities say
was in her 20s,

08:44.290 --> 08:46.820
Remains unidentified.

08:46.820 --> 08:48.860
The police
have identified the man,

08:48.860 --> 08:50.260
Who has multiple tattoos,

08:50.260 --> 08:52.830
As 29-year-old drew cataldi,

08:52.830 --> 08:54.760
A drug dealer
with prior convictions,

08:54.760 --> 08:56.530
From nevada.

08:56.530 --> 08:58.300
Well, we're currently
looking for witnesses,

08:58.300 --> 09:01.270
Anyone who might have
seen or heard anything.

09:01.270 --> 09:02.640
[♪]

09:02.640 --> 09:05.910
That anyone with information
about this crime,

09:05.910 --> 09:07.540
Or has seen
something suspicious...

09:13.710 --> 09:15.880
[horn honks]

09:21.190 --> 09:22.660
I got us a room

09:22.660 --> 09:23.890
At a motel about
15 minutes from here.

09:23.890 --> 09:24.990
We'll get rid of
the bloody stuff

09:24.990 --> 09:26.030
On the way.

09:26.030 --> 09:27.260
You're driving
around with it?

09:27.260 --> 09:28.700
Well, I couldn't
leave it at the house!

09:28.700 --> 09:30.660
Oh, my god.

09:30.670 --> 09:33.570
[highway traffic droning nearby]

09:38.210 --> 09:40.210
-I want to call my dad.
-No!

09:40.210 --> 09:41.710
No one can know about this.

09:41.710 --> 09:43.910
He'll know what to do, rick!
He'll help us.

09:43.910 --> 09:45.110
Let's just go.

09:45.110 --> 09:46.810
If we drive
straight through,

09:46.820 --> 09:48.080
We can be in seattle
in less than two days.

09:48.080 --> 09:49.350
Okay, baby.

09:49.350 --> 09:51.750
If that's what you want,
that's what we'll do.

09:51.750 --> 09:52.920
[panting tensely]

09:52.920 --> 09:54.850
[♪]

09:54.860 --> 09:57.660
Did you pay for this room
with your credit card?

09:57.660 --> 09:58.990
I didn't have any cash on me.

09:58.990 --> 10:01.090
We've gotta get outta here!

10:01.100 --> 10:02.230
[siren chirps]

10:02.230 --> 10:04.100
This is anderson p.D.

10:04.100 --> 10:06.230
We have the motel surrounded...

10:06.230 --> 10:08.130
Okay, baby, we gotta
stick together.

10:08.140 --> 10:10.740
Okay? We're all
we've got.

10:10.740 --> 10:11.910
I love you.

10:11.910 --> 10:13.740
I love you, too.

10:18.210 --> 10:21.180
[clears his throat quietly]

10:21.180 --> 10:22.980
So...

10:22.990 --> 10:24.120
We recovered the shotgun

10:24.120 --> 10:25.850
From the motel room.

10:25.850 --> 10:28.190
I have told you
three times already,

10:28.190 --> 10:30.660
Rick put it under the bed.

10:31.730 --> 10:34.130
And then we went
to the sporting goods store

10:34.130 --> 10:36.360
Where the gun was purchased
and...

10:36.370 --> 10:38.930
They have
a credit card receipt

10:38.930 --> 10:40.070
With your
signature on it.

10:40.070 --> 10:41.740
You bought the gun.

10:41.740 --> 10:43.400
Rick told me to.

10:43.410 --> 10:44.900
You see how it looks?

10:44.910 --> 10:46.140
Rick had told me

10:46.140 --> 10:47.840
That there was something
about his past

10:47.840 --> 10:49.210
That wouldn't allow him
to buy it.

10:49.210 --> 10:50.680
He wanted a shotgun!

10:50.680 --> 10:52.010
Just the day
before the murders,

10:52.010 --> 10:54.280
He decides that
he's got to have a gun?

10:54.280 --> 10:57.320
I-I don't know.
It-- it wasn't planned.

10:57.320 --> 11:00.290
Did rick hull tell you
why he shot ms. Nordman?

11:00.290 --> 11:01.890
Self-defense.

11:01.890 --> 11:03.290
Self-defense?

11:03.290 --> 11:05.990
Self-defense explains
one shot, to drew,

11:05.990 --> 11:07.830
But how do you explain
the other two?

11:07.830 --> 11:09.330
And how do you explain

11:09.330 --> 11:12.100
A 110-pound woman
threatening

11:12.100 --> 11:16.000
A guy who's almost 200 pounds
and armed with a shotgun?

11:16.000 --> 11:17.170
Why do I have to explain?

11:17.170 --> 11:18.300
I wasn't there!

11:18.310 --> 11:19.810
You didn't go to the police.

11:19.810 --> 11:21.680
I was scared.
Rick manipulated me.

11:21.680 --> 11:24.140
Oh, did he threaten you?
Did he hurt you?

11:24.150 --> 11:25.380
No.

11:25.380 --> 11:26.750
And then
when he dropped you off,

11:26.750 --> 11:28.310
You could've
told someone, anyone.

11:28.320 --> 11:29.350
You had all day.

11:29.350 --> 11:30.950
I was scared!

11:30.950 --> 11:33.320
I didn't know what to do.
I'd never seen a carcass before.

11:37.320 --> 11:39.230
I think...

11:39.230 --> 11:42.260
That you wanted to
get rid of cataldi.

11:42.260 --> 11:44.060
-That's why you bought the gun.
-No.

11:44.070 --> 11:46.700
Sarah, let me tell you
how I think this went down.

11:46.700 --> 11:50.070
I think you waited
till rick got really messed up.

11:50.070 --> 11:51.240
This is insane!

11:51.240 --> 11:52.840
You're gonna do it
my way or we're done!

11:52.840 --> 11:54.070
Okay.

11:54.080 --> 11:55.910
You said you'd always
protect me, now prove it!

11:55.910 --> 11:57.840
[trish screaming]

12:00.250 --> 12:01.350
She can't live.

12:02.850 --> 12:04.420
[sobbing]

12:04.420 --> 12:05.890
[shot echoes]

12:05.890 --> 12:08.760
You're twisting everything!
Rick killed them.

12:08.760 --> 12:09.820
Because you made him do it.

12:09.830 --> 12:10.960
That is a lie!

12:10.960 --> 12:13.090
I wasn't there!
I went for cigarettes!

12:13.100 --> 12:14.360
No one saw you.

12:14.360 --> 12:15.800
There's no cigarettes,
there's no receipt.

12:15.800 --> 12:18.100
I changed my mind,
it was late.

12:18.100 --> 12:20.400
I got scared,
I decided to go back home.

12:20.400 --> 12:22.500
Trish is my friend.

12:22.500 --> 12:25.170
Well, who refers
to their friend as a "carcass?"

12:25.170 --> 12:26.470
Sarah pender,

12:26.480 --> 12:28.370
You have the right
to remain silent.

12:28.380 --> 12:29.780
Anything you say
can, and will be,

12:29.780 --> 12:31.040
Used against you
in a court of law.

12:32.950 --> 12:35.320
[♪]

12:36.520 --> 12:38.320
Hello.

12:40.450 --> 12:43.020
[♪]

12:43.020 --> 12:47.360
You're that chick
they say killed her roommates.

12:47.360 --> 12:50.530
You and your boyfriend
threw 'em in a dumpster.

12:50.530 --> 12:53.400
Could you give it a rest,
okay, roxanne?

12:53.400 --> 12:54.470
Ignore her, honey.

12:54.470 --> 12:57.240
[♪]

12:57.240 --> 12:58.540
Oh, great. Great.

12:58.540 --> 13:00.010
Look what
you did. Huh?

13:00.010 --> 13:01.310
People who live in sin

13:01.310 --> 13:03.480
Shouldn't throw stones, 'kay?

13:03.480 --> 13:05.280
Well, that don't even
make any sense.

13:05.280 --> 13:07.280
[sarah sobs]

13:07.280 --> 13:09.220
Oh, no, honey, look.

13:09.220 --> 13:11.520
You're gonna be fine.
Okay?

13:11.520 --> 13:12.850
It's not that bad here.

13:12.850 --> 13:16.920
Why don't you just
get some rest?

13:18.190 --> 13:20.490
[♪]

13:30.400 --> 13:33.410
[♪]

13:49.520 --> 13:52.530
[♪]

13:56.030 --> 13:58.000
Use the phone, daddy.

13:59.370 --> 14:02.300
Sarah... Are you okay?

14:02.300 --> 14:04.600
What are you
doing here?

14:04.610 --> 14:06.340
I got here
as soon as I could.

14:06.340 --> 14:10.080
Oh, daddy...

14:10.080 --> 14:11.580
It's gonna be okay.

14:11.580 --> 14:13.480
This is a sick misunderstanding.

14:13.480 --> 14:15.220
I've hired an attorney.

14:15.220 --> 14:16.620
I want to
go home with you.

14:16.620 --> 14:19.250
Yes. When this nightmare
is over,

14:19.250 --> 14:20.290
You're coming home.

14:20.290 --> 14:22.390
I don't belong in here.

14:22.390 --> 14:24.190
When are they gonna let me out?

14:24.190 --> 14:28.160
They're charging you
with a double murder, sarah.

14:29.400 --> 14:31.160
There is no bail.

14:33.930 --> 14:35.940
I'm sorry.

14:35.940 --> 14:38.200
There's nothing
to be afraid of, okay?

14:38.210 --> 14:39.970
Arraignments are simple.

14:39.980 --> 14:41.240
Your lawyer's
gonna enter your plea.

14:41.240 --> 14:43.140
You won't have to speak.

14:43.140 --> 14:44.880
I wish you could
be there.

14:44.880 --> 14:46.880
[guard]: Jamie long, let's go.
You just made bail.

14:46.880 --> 14:49.280
[jamie]: Yeah. Can I have
a minute to say goodbye?

14:49.280 --> 14:50.450
I don't think
I can do this.

14:50.450 --> 14:52.490
Listen to me.

14:52.490 --> 14:54.520
You need to think
positive things.

14:54.520 --> 14:55.990
All right?
Like that old song.

14:55.990 --> 14:58.120
Raindrops and roses,
and kitten-whiskers,

14:58.130 --> 14:59.290
And puppy-breath?

14:59.290 --> 15:00.930
You're crazy.

15:00.930 --> 15:03.160
You're gonna be
all right, honey.

15:03.160 --> 15:06.630
This nightmare is gonna
be over really soon,

15:06.640 --> 15:08.670
And I'll bring you
whatever you want--

15:08.670 --> 15:10.900
Books, candy, whatever.

15:10.910 --> 15:13.210
I'll never forget
this, jamie.

15:15.040 --> 15:17.580
[♪]

15:17.580 --> 15:19.950
[cell door rumbles open]

15:24.550 --> 15:26.950
To be sweet, innocent,
likable...

15:26.960 --> 15:28.520
But lurking within her
is a demon

15:28.520 --> 15:30.520
With the ability
to seduce another

15:30.530 --> 15:32.490
To commit
the most atrocious act.

15:32.490 --> 15:34.960
She's like
a female charles manson.

15:34.960 --> 15:36.230
This whole trial's
just a farce.

15:36.230 --> 15:37.660
Things that they're
accusing her of doing,

15:37.670 --> 15:40.300
My baby
is not capable of.

15:40.300 --> 15:42.540
If anyone was
manipulating anyone,

15:42.540 --> 15:44.600
It's that boyfriend,
richard hull.

15:44.610 --> 15:46.040
He's the one with
the criminal record.

15:46.040 --> 15:47.340
Doesn't matter
what they say about me.

15:47.340 --> 15:48.940
Sarah.

15:48.940 --> 15:50.710
Last night, during
a sweep of mr. Hull's cell,

15:50.710 --> 15:52.350
They discovered a letter.

15:52.350 --> 15:53.550
A letter from rick?

15:53.550 --> 15:55.450
A letter to mr. Hull
from sarah.

15:55.450 --> 15:57.180
I haven't written
any letters to rick.

15:57.190 --> 15:58.250
"my dearest richard,

15:58.250 --> 15:59.320
"I love you

15:59.320 --> 16:00.990
"and I miss you so much.

16:00.990 --> 16:02.190
"I wish I could go back

16:02.190 --> 16:04.090
"and change the events
of that night.

16:04.090 --> 16:06.590
"maybe it was
all the pot we smoked,

16:06.590 --> 16:07.730
"or the booze,

16:07.730 --> 16:10.000
"but I just snapped.

16:10.000 --> 16:11.730
"I'm sorry I lied
about not being there.

16:11.730 --> 16:13.470
Love always,
your lady bear."

16:13.470 --> 16:15.540
That is a lie!
I-I didn't write that.

16:15.540 --> 16:18.170
I wasn't there
when rick shot them!

16:18.170 --> 16:20.340
I went for a walk!

16:20.340 --> 16:21.610
This-- this is not
my handwriting!

16:21.610 --> 16:23.380
You... You have to
believe me, mr. Brady.

16:23.380 --> 16:25.040
Rick is lying.

16:25.050 --> 16:27.580
I don't have to believe you,
sarah, the jury does.

16:27.580 --> 16:28.650
They have already heard

16:28.650 --> 16:30.450
That you bought
the murder weapon

16:30.450 --> 16:32.990
And that you helped mr. Hull
dispose of the bodies.

16:32.990 --> 16:36.120
This letter
is very damaging.

16:36.120 --> 16:37.690
[sighs, deflating]

16:40.390 --> 16:43.200
[♪]

16:44.400 --> 16:49.140
Sarah pender was found guilty
of two counts of homicide

16:49.140 --> 16:52.010
And sentenced to 50 years
for the murder of mr. Cataldi,

16:52.010 --> 16:53.740
And 60 years for ms. Nordman,

16:53.740 --> 16:57.610
Sentences running consecutively
for 110 years.

16:57.610 --> 17:00.310
[♪]

17:09.690 --> 17:13.030
[♪]

17:22.800 --> 17:24.599
I'm superintendent rogers.

17:24.609 --> 17:28.240
You may call me "ma'am"
or "ms. Rogers."

17:28.240 --> 17:29.510
Yes, ma'am.

17:29.510 --> 17:32.680
Well, sarah pender...
You're home.

17:32.680 --> 17:35.620
[♪]

17:48.460 --> 17:50.330
[rogers]: Life at rockville
is structured.

17:50.330 --> 17:52.570
No one gets
special treatment.

17:52.570 --> 17:53.770
We do count twice a day--

17:53.770 --> 17:56.300
8:50 a.M.,
and at 3:50 in the p.M.

17:56.300 --> 17:58.600
Unless you're at your job,
in a classroom,

17:58.610 --> 18:00.210
Or in the infirmary,

18:00.210 --> 18:02.380
Every offender must be
in her cell on her bunk

18:02.380 --> 18:04.310
For count.

18:14.590 --> 18:16.520
[♪]

18:24.570 --> 18:26.400
[deadbolt clunks]

18:26.400 --> 18:28.270
Name's corinne.

18:28.270 --> 18:29.640
You're up top.

18:29.640 --> 18:32.510
Do not step on my bed
getting up or down.

18:32.510 --> 18:34.410
Do not kick me.

18:34.410 --> 18:36.140
We clean on Sunday.

18:36.140 --> 18:39.750
And don't ask
no stupid questions.

18:40.850 --> 18:43.880
[♪]

18:49.420 --> 18:51.890
Hey! What part of
"do not step on my bed"

18:51.890 --> 18:54.330
Don't you understand?

18:55.300 --> 18:57.360
Want me to come up there
and beat you down

18:57.370 --> 18:59.670
On the first day in?

18:59.670 --> 19:02.840
[♪]

19:14.520 --> 19:17.450
[♪]

19:24.360 --> 19:25.590
[snaps]

19:29.900 --> 19:32.230
[♪]

19:34.940 --> 19:37.400
Hey. I'm mimi.

19:37.410 --> 19:39.570
But everybody
calls me "mimi."

19:39.570 --> 19:43.410
Forgery,
selling fake I.D.S,

19:43.410 --> 19:47.350
But my lawyer says
I'll only do 18 months,

19:47.350 --> 19:48.880
So I've got, like, nine to go.

19:48.880 --> 19:50.750
Do you want
to hang out sometime?

19:50.750 --> 19:53.850
I'm friends with
your cellie, corinne.

19:53.860 --> 19:58.860
Do you know
she poisoned two husbands?

20:00.460 --> 20:02.360
She did.

20:02.360 --> 20:04.830
Okay. Tsk.

20:06.400 --> 20:08.570
[mimi sighs]

20:09.870 --> 20:11.700
Sarah jo pender,
get over here!

20:11.710 --> 20:13.740
[relieved laugh]

20:13.740 --> 20:15.370
I thought you forgot
about me.

20:15.380 --> 20:17.910
Oh, my gosh, no.
What'd I tell you?

20:17.910 --> 20:19.880
The first day you could
have visitors,

20:19.880 --> 20:22.250
I would be here,
with bells on.

20:22.250 --> 20:23.680
[bracelets jangling]

20:23.690 --> 20:25.650
So, sunshine...

20:25.650 --> 20:27.390
How you doing?

20:27.390 --> 20:30.760
Uh, it's okay.
I'm reading, sleeping a lot.

20:30.760 --> 20:33.330
What about friends?

20:34.560 --> 20:36.360
Sarah...

20:36.360 --> 20:40.270
Your father
has hired an attorney

20:40.270 --> 20:41.630
Who specializes
in appeals.

20:41.640 --> 20:43.500
Yeah, I didn't get
adequate representation.

20:43.500 --> 20:45.970
We're going to
get you out of here,

20:45.970 --> 20:47.910
But it's going to
take time.

20:47.910 --> 20:49.810
You've got to
realize that.

20:49.810 --> 20:51.610
I'm not gonna make it in here.

20:51.610 --> 20:53.710
Yes, you will.

20:53.720 --> 20:54.980
Now, listen.

20:54.980 --> 20:56.820
Time's gonna go
a whole lot faster

20:56.820 --> 20:59.990
If you don't just sit around
feeling sorry for yourself.

20:59.990 --> 21:02.420
Do we understand
each other?

21:04.490 --> 21:06.430
Sarah?
Look at me.

21:07.830 --> 21:10.530
You've gotta do your part.

21:12.970 --> 21:15.700
[♪]

21:30.650 --> 21:33.590
[♪]

21:54.570 --> 21:57.680
[♪]

22:00.710 --> 22:02.850
Excuse me.

22:02.850 --> 22:04.080
Sorry.

22:04.090 --> 22:06.390
Hey. Hi. I'm farrell.

22:06.390 --> 22:09.390
I was hoping you could
tell me what this means.

22:09.390 --> 22:11.760
I'm busy right now.
Sorry.

22:11.760 --> 22:13.060
Please?

22:13.060 --> 22:14.030
No one'll help me,

22:14.030 --> 22:15.630
And someone said

22:15.630 --> 22:18.060
You're the smartest
girl in here.

22:18.070 --> 22:19.970
It's something to do
with my kids.

22:24.910 --> 22:28.440
It's a petition
for guardianship.

22:28.440 --> 22:29.910
They want to
take your kids away.

22:29.910 --> 22:32.040
Who?

22:32.050 --> 22:34.050
I'm a good mom.

22:34.050 --> 22:36.050
I've made
some mistakes,

22:36.050 --> 22:38.080
But I'm a good mom.

22:39.390 --> 22:41.090
Who are
gladys and george brenner?

22:41.090 --> 22:42.760
My aunt and uncle.

22:42.760 --> 22:45.860
I asked them to watch the girls
until I get released.

22:45.860 --> 22:48.530
They're asking the court to
terminate your parental rights

22:48.530 --> 22:49.800
And name them legal guardians.

22:49.800 --> 22:51.360
Can they do that?

22:51.370 --> 22:54.000
Let me see what I can do.

22:54.000 --> 22:56.840
[gasps]

22:56.840 --> 22:58.770
[♪]

23:02.080 --> 23:05.140
[singing loudly]:
♪ daisy, daisy

23:05.150 --> 23:08.550
♪ give me your answer, do

23:08.550 --> 23:09.950
Shut up!

23:09.950 --> 23:11.680
It's a free country!

23:11.690 --> 23:14.120
♪ I'm half crazy

23:14.120 --> 23:16.560
♪ all for the love of you

23:16.560 --> 23:19.460
[woman]: Girl, you are
full-on crazy.

23:19.460 --> 23:22.760
Some people just have
no appreciation of music.

23:22.760 --> 23:25.500
She speaks.

23:27.130 --> 23:29.570
♪ daisy, daisy

23:29.570 --> 23:32.070
♪ give me your answer, do

23:32.070 --> 23:34.740
[cell mates chatting]

23:36.040 --> 23:39.750
[♪]

23:39.750 --> 23:43.780
Well, if it isn't
miss charlotte manson.

23:43.790 --> 23:45.850
Happy Halloween.
Cocktail?

23:49.820 --> 23:50.920
[gags]: Oh!

23:50.930 --> 23:52.460
What the hell is this?

23:52.460 --> 23:54.730
Mimi's specialty--
"cafe karma."

23:54.730 --> 23:58.900
Little bit of sugar, coffee
and dihexadryl.

23:58.900 --> 24:03.600
Gets you a nice caffeine-sugar
antihistamine buzz,

24:03.600 --> 24:06.070
And your nose won't run
for a week.

24:06.070 --> 24:08.510
[laughs] they let you
have dihexadryl in here?

24:08.510 --> 24:09.780
No!

24:09.780 --> 24:12.880
I got a friendly guard
who helps me get it.

24:12.880 --> 24:14.450
By "friendly,"

24:14.450 --> 24:16.720
She means she rocks his world
every other week.

24:16.720 --> 24:17.780
Ga-bown! Ga-bown!

24:17.790 --> 24:20.750
You know
what I'm saying?

24:20.760 --> 24:22.890
[laughter spreads]

24:25.030 --> 24:27.890
[hip-hop playing]

25:11.240 --> 25:12.840
They never
notified you about

25:12.840 --> 25:15.170
A hearing to determine
parental rights.

25:15.180 --> 25:16.880
How could I have
gone to a hearing?

25:16.880 --> 25:17.980
I was locked up
in here.

25:17.980 --> 25:18.980
Doesn't matter.

25:18.980 --> 25:19.950
According to the law,

25:19.950 --> 25:21.210
The state mandates

25:21.220 --> 25:22.280
That both parents
must be notified

25:22.280 --> 25:23.820
Of parental termination,

25:23.820 --> 25:26.220
Unless their whereabouts
are "unknown."

25:26.220 --> 25:27.820
Do they know
your whereabouts?

25:27.820 --> 25:29.150
You think?

25:29.160 --> 25:31.090
That's why they're trying
to take my kids from me.

25:31.090 --> 25:32.260
Well, they blew it.

25:32.260 --> 25:34.830
We're gonna get
your kids back, farrell.

25:34.830 --> 25:37.160
[laughs, relieved]

25:37.160 --> 25:39.770
[squeals]

25:43.300 --> 25:46.170
[♪]

25:48.310 --> 25:49.840
Come give
your dad a hug.

25:49.840 --> 25:52.580
Oh! I didn't think I'd get
a visit until christmas.

25:52.580 --> 25:55.610
God, I miss this.
Hugging you.

25:55.620 --> 25:56.980
How are you?

25:56.980 --> 25:59.220
I'm fine.

25:59.220 --> 26:00.820
I'm not gonna let them
get me down.

26:00.820 --> 26:05.090
Most people in your situation
would've given up.

26:05.090 --> 26:07.030
What's wrong?

26:07.030 --> 26:08.290
[sighing]

26:08.300 --> 26:11.760
The appellate court
denied your appeal.

26:11.770 --> 26:15.030
Didn't find anything wrong
with mr. Brady's representation.

26:15.040 --> 26:16.270
But...

26:16.270 --> 26:20.010
[exhales in shock,
then sighs]

26:20.010 --> 26:22.070
Okay.

26:22.080 --> 26:24.840
Okay, this is just a setback.

26:24.850 --> 26:28.080
I've already done two years
for a crime I didn't commit.

26:28.080 --> 26:29.280
I'm fighting
a system

26:29.280 --> 26:30.720
That won't admit
it made a mistake.

26:30.720 --> 26:32.120
There are all sorts
of appeals I can make.

26:32.120 --> 26:34.990
Harsh and excessive punishment,
insufficient evidence.

26:34.990 --> 26:36.920
If they want a fight,
they're gonna get one.

26:38.830 --> 26:39.890
What?

26:39.890 --> 26:43.060
You would've made
a great lawyer.

26:43.060 --> 26:44.730
You've got such a sharp mind.

26:44.730 --> 26:47.270
I'm going to find something,
some way to get out of this.

26:47.270 --> 26:49.230
[takes a deep breath]

26:49.240 --> 26:52.140
The thing is...

26:52.140 --> 26:53.910
I'm short on cash.

26:53.910 --> 26:55.170
That's okay, daddy.

26:55.180 --> 26:58.240
Okay? You've done enough.

26:58.250 --> 27:00.250
Just please don't
give up on me.

27:00.250 --> 27:02.950
Never, baby. Never.

27:14.330 --> 27:16.060
We got to get your guy

27:16.060 --> 27:17.300
To bring in
more dihexadryl,

27:17.300 --> 27:18.660
And you've gotta stop
giving it away.

27:18.670 --> 27:19.930
These girls are hooked.

27:19.930 --> 27:21.200
They're gonna pay a lot
to get a buzz on.

27:21.200 --> 27:22.670
But there's no money
allowed in here.

27:22.670 --> 27:24.100
The money stays
on the outside--

27:24.110 --> 27:25.300
Money orders.

27:25.310 --> 27:26.740
Someone on the outside
cashes 'em,

27:26.740 --> 27:28.210
Opens up
a bank account.

27:28.210 --> 27:30.180
Maybe we can
even save enough

27:30.180 --> 27:32.040
To get you
singing lessons.

27:33.850 --> 27:35.310
Mooney v. Holohan.

27:35.320 --> 27:37.380
Mooney had been pardoned

27:37.390 --> 27:38.980
When he proved
he'd been convicted

27:38.990 --> 27:40.790
On the basis of evidence
known by the state to be false.

27:40.790 --> 27:43.420
Like jamie long told you
on the phone, mr. Cook,

27:43.420 --> 27:45.960
Rick wrote to me
that he had a change of heart.

27:45.960 --> 27:49.230
My supposed
"confession letter" was fake.

27:49.230 --> 27:50.660
They have to let me out,

27:50.670 --> 27:52.130
Or at least give me
a new trial.

27:52.130 --> 27:54.100
To get post-
conviction relief,

27:54.100 --> 27:55.370
You can't just show

27:55.370 --> 27:57.700
That some of the evidence
against you was false--

27:57.710 --> 27:59.910
You have to show
reasonable innocence.

27:59.910 --> 28:01.310
I am innocent.

28:01.310 --> 28:02.710
It's a long shot.

28:02.710 --> 28:04.740
It's my only shot.

28:05.980 --> 28:08.380
You're gonna need
mr. Hull to sign an affidavit

28:08.380 --> 28:10.020
Stating that
he forged that letter.

28:10.020 --> 28:12.120
Rick will do anything
to help me.

28:12.120 --> 28:14.020
Okay, this is your last chance

28:14.020 --> 28:16.460
To have your conviction
overturned, ms. Pender.

28:16.460 --> 28:18.260
It could take
a couple of years,

28:18.260 --> 28:20.260
Which means
a lot of time.

28:20.260 --> 28:21.430
I'm expensive.

28:21.430 --> 28:24.830
Don't worry.
I'll get you your money.

28:26.300 --> 28:28.270
You need to talk
to your guy.

28:28.270 --> 28:30.200
He quit.

28:30.200 --> 28:32.070
He can't quit.
He's in too deep.

28:32.070 --> 28:33.770
He's gone.

28:33.770 --> 28:35.410
He doesn't work here
anymore.

28:35.410 --> 28:36.980
Well, we need to
find a new mule.

28:36.980 --> 28:41.250
Sarah...
I can't risk it.

28:41.250 --> 28:44.120
I'm getting out
in a few weeks.

28:44.120 --> 28:45.720
You're right.

28:45.720 --> 28:47.290
We can't do anything
to jeopardize your release.

28:47.290 --> 28:49.120
I understand.

28:49.120 --> 28:52.120
Mr. Cook has agreed
to let me pay his retainer

28:52.130 --> 28:54.160
A few hundred bucks at a time,

28:54.160 --> 28:56.330
But ben and me are tapped out.

28:56.330 --> 28:58.400
Do you want me
to call your father?

28:58.400 --> 29:00.300
No, no.
I've cost him enough already.

29:00.300 --> 29:02.030
More money will come.

29:02.040 --> 29:03.770
I'm exploring
some other options.

29:03.770 --> 29:06.940
Okay, folks.
Visitation hours are over.

29:06.940 --> 29:09.410
I love you
more than puppy paws.

29:09.410 --> 29:10.940
Kindly make your way
to the exit.

29:10.950 --> 29:12.880
Sweet baby.

29:16.380 --> 29:18.180
Time to go.

29:18.190 --> 29:20.220
Line it up, ladies.

29:20.220 --> 29:22.490
[♪]

29:25.460 --> 29:28.190
[♪]

29:32.770 --> 29:34.330
You know, this would
go a lot faster

29:34.340 --> 29:36.100
If you lent a hand.

29:36.100 --> 29:39.070
[♪]

29:40.810 --> 29:42.170
Okay, write this down.

29:42.180 --> 29:45.980
It includes actions
for recovery of specific--

29:45.980 --> 29:48.850
[p.A. Crackles]: White,
hernandez, pender,

29:48.850 --> 29:51.220
Report to the chemical closet
of the rec building

29:51.220 --> 29:52.420
For custodian duty.

29:52.420 --> 29:55.090
We'll do this later.

29:55.090 --> 29:58.490
[♪]

30:14.110 --> 30:16.410
[lock clicks]

30:16.410 --> 30:17.980
[spitler sighs]

30:17.980 --> 30:20.980
I had to call in a favor
to get you this detail.

30:20.980 --> 30:22.180
[puts keys down]

30:22.180 --> 30:23.580
Hope it's worth it.

30:23.580 --> 30:26.050
What makes you think
I won't scream?

30:27.150 --> 30:28.120
[gasps]

30:32.060 --> 30:34.260
[sarah gasps]

30:34.260 --> 30:36.200
Did you bring a condom?

30:38.400 --> 30:40.870
Sorry, no glove,
no love.

30:42.470 --> 30:45.270
[♪]

30:45.270 --> 30:47.270
[intense gasping
and wheezing]

30:47.270 --> 30:48.370
Help! It's mimi!

30:48.380 --> 30:49.880
Something's wrong.

30:49.880 --> 30:52.180
[wheezing intensely]

30:54.310 --> 30:57.020
Guard! Guard!

30:58.220 --> 31:00.390
[hushed]: Look at me.
Never forget who helped you.

31:00.390 --> 31:02.020
[gasping]

31:02.020 --> 31:03.890
Sarah, look out.
Look out, look out, look out.

31:03.890 --> 31:05.360
Mimi? Mimi?
Can you hear me?

31:05.360 --> 31:06.560
Nod if you can hear me.

31:06.560 --> 31:09.060
Stacy, go get
the medical staff, now.

31:09.060 --> 31:12.300
[spitler consoles mimi
as she hyperventilates]

31:18.070 --> 31:20.370
So I talked to ms. Rogers.
Mimi's gonna be okay.

31:20.370 --> 31:22.140
They're going to keep her
in the infirmary

31:22.140 --> 31:23.410
Until she's released
next month.

31:23.410 --> 31:25.940
Apparently, she had
an allergic reaction.

31:25.950 --> 31:28.050
Allergic reaction,
my ass.

31:28.050 --> 31:29.250
I told her that girl,

31:29.250 --> 31:30.650
She keep drinking
that cafe karma,

31:30.650 --> 31:32.120
She gonna kill herself.

31:32.120 --> 31:34.520
She's just lucky she had
you there to help her.

31:34.520 --> 31:35.990
I don't eat meat.

31:35.990 --> 31:38.160
[meatballs plop down]

31:42.100 --> 31:45.260
Is this really
the fight you want to have?

31:50.570 --> 31:53.070
[♪]

31:56.910 --> 31:59.210
[♪]

32:02.420 --> 32:04.380
[condom packet crinkles]

32:04.390 --> 32:06.550
Come here.

32:06.550 --> 32:08.290
Mm.

32:08.290 --> 32:12.190
You must have played
sports in high school.

32:12.190 --> 32:13.230
Wrestling.

32:13.230 --> 32:15.130
Mm-mm-mm.

32:15.130 --> 32:19.160
What, are you gonna pin me,
officer spitler?

32:25.370 --> 32:28.440
[♪]

32:28.440 --> 32:29.640
[tray thuds]

32:29.640 --> 32:31.110
Look... [sighs]

32:31.110 --> 32:33.110
Nobody cares if
you keep to yourself,

32:33.110 --> 32:35.080
But you've got to decide
what you care about.

32:35.080 --> 32:37.180
You don't know nothin'
about my situation.

32:37.180 --> 32:38.950
I know about
this situation.

32:38.950 --> 32:40.720
A few years ago,
I was you.

32:40.720 --> 32:42.350
You gotta find
something to do,

32:42.360 --> 32:45.220
You need to get a job,
you have to have a plan.

32:45.230 --> 32:46.290
It's gonna help
pass the time.

32:46.290 --> 32:47.530
I'm not gonna
work for them.

32:47.530 --> 32:49.430
Not for them.
For you.

32:54.600 --> 32:56.200
[cutlery scraping tray]

33:00.410 --> 33:03.280
I heard they need
a new girl in the laundry.

33:06.610 --> 33:08.610
[moaning]

33:08.620 --> 33:12.020
[gasping and panting]

33:15.120 --> 33:18.520
I have never felt this way
with anyone before.

33:18.530 --> 33:20.190
This connection.

33:20.190 --> 33:23.060
I walk around
with this pit in my stomach.

33:23.060 --> 33:25.060
Night-time's the worst.

33:25.070 --> 33:27.370
Sometimes, I can't sleep.

33:27.370 --> 33:30.240
You know,
if you could get me a phone,

33:30.240 --> 33:33.110
You could tuck me in at night.

33:33.110 --> 33:35.110
We could have phone sex.

33:35.110 --> 33:37.140
[she giggles flirtatiously]

33:37.140 --> 33:39.610
You have
a one-track mind.

33:39.610 --> 33:41.750
I know. It's dumb.

33:41.750 --> 33:43.550
You can't get me a phone.

33:45.420 --> 33:49.450
Baby-doll,
I can get you anything you want.

33:50.790 --> 33:53.430
[♪]

33:58.700 --> 34:00.500
[jamie]: Hello?

34:00.500 --> 34:02.070
[quietly]: Happy new year's.
It's sarah.

34:02.070 --> 34:03.770
Oh, my god!

34:03.770 --> 34:05.570
Sarah? Oh, my... God!

34:05.570 --> 34:07.740
Shh. Calm down.
I only have a minute.

34:07.740 --> 34:10.239
I've made a friend--

34:10.239 --> 34:12.110
-...Who's gonna help us.
-Who?

34:12.110 --> 34:13.550
Someone else
who believes in me.

34:13.550 --> 34:15.380
I'm gonna text you

34:15.380 --> 34:16.820
A list of
stuff to buy--

34:16.820 --> 34:19.179
Phones, dihexadryl,
tobacco.

34:19.190 --> 34:20.550
N-- sarah, no, no.

34:20.550 --> 34:22.219
I'm not smuggling
anything in there.

34:22.219 --> 34:24.120
I would never ask you
to break the law.

34:24.120 --> 34:26.389
Dihexadryl's an over-the-counter
antihistamine.

34:26.389 --> 34:28.159
I've got it all worked out.

34:28.159 --> 34:29.460
I take the orders.

34:29.460 --> 34:31.330
The girls get someone
on the outside

34:31.330 --> 34:34.699
To send a money order
to your p.O. Box.

34:34.699 --> 34:36.739
You just deposit the money
into a bank account,

34:36.739 --> 34:39.300
Then you go to
one of those chain drugstores.

34:39.310 --> 34:40.770
They're gonna have
everything on the list.

34:40.770 --> 34:43.739
You buy it and you ship it
to a different p.O. Box,

34:43.739 --> 34:45.280
All legal.

34:45.280 --> 34:47.409
Sarah, this is gonna
mess with your appeal.

34:47.409 --> 34:49.280
This is gonna pay
for my appeal.

34:49.280 --> 34:50.580
Don't worry.

34:50.580 --> 34:51.820
I love you
more than

34:51.820 --> 34:55.150
Fairy dust
on butterfly wings.

34:55.159 --> 34:58.620
[♪]

35:53.150 --> 35:54.680
[gasping]

35:54.680 --> 35:57.180
Happy valentine's day.

36:02.360 --> 36:04.790
You were wrong, mr. Cook.

36:04.790 --> 36:06.930
It only took them one year
to review my case.

36:06.930 --> 36:08.660
When's my retrial?

36:08.660 --> 36:11.530
Your motion was denied.

36:11.530 --> 36:13.830
What?

36:13.830 --> 36:15.670
But rick's affidavit

36:15.670 --> 36:18.800
The judge has denied
your request for a retrial

36:18.810 --> 36:21.810
Based on the other undisputed
evidence against you-

36:21.810 --> 36:24.210
The shotgun you purchased,

36:24.210 --> 36:25.610
The truck you borrowed,

36:25.610 --> 36:27.810
Forensic evidence
at your house.

36:27.810 --> 36:30.650
You're not
getting out, sarah.

36:30.650 --> 36:32.180
I'm sorry.

36:32.190 --> 36:34.290
You're sorry?

36:34.290 --> 36:36.690
I've paid you
thousands of dollars!

36:36.690 --> 36:40.460
People have made sacrifices
for me! No! No!

36:40.460 --> 36:42.760
[sarah sobbing and raging]

36:44.630 --> 36:47.800
Let go! Let me go!

36:47.800 --> 36:50.370
[continues raging]

36:51.970 --> 36:54.310
[weeping]

36:56.940 --> 36:59.610
[♪]

37:05.590 --> 37:08.250
[muffled rageful screaming]

37:11.720 --> 37:14.390
[♪]

37:23.800 --> 37:25.570
[lock clunks open]

37:28.910 --> 37:30.410
I hope you won't let

37:30.410 --> 37:31.810
This monumental
disappointment

37:31.810 --> 37:32.810
Change
your attitude.

37:32.810 --> 37:35.010
No, ma'am.

37:35.020 --> 37:36.510
I'm not sure you realize

37:36.520 --> 37:38.580
What a positive role model
you've become.

37:39.990 --> 37:41.490
Thank you, ma'am.

37:41.490 --> 37:43.590
I'm gonna bring
my girls to meet you.

37:43.590 --> 37:44.990
No. No, farrell.

37:44.990 --> 37:46.590
You need to
forget about me,

37:46.590 --> 37:47.760
You need to
forget this place,

37:47.760 --> 37:50.660
And focus on staying
the hell away from here.

37:58.040 --> 38:00.740
A picture for your wall.

38:03.040 --> 38:05.440
Oh, they're beautiful.

38:05.450 --> 38:07.650
I always wanted
a big family.

38:07.650 --> 38:10.520
Two-storey house,
lots of yard,

38:10.520 --> 38:12.850
And five or six kids
running around.

38:15.020 --> 38:18.020
Let's see...

38:18.030 --> 38:20.890
[♪]

38:24.660 --> 38:26.930
I hardly recognize you
in those clothes.

38:26.930 --> 38:29.930
How can I thank you
for getting my kids back?

38:29.940 --> 38:31.970
Don't lose them again.

38:31.970 --> 38:33.540
They need you.

38:35.740 --> 38:37.540
We have to go.

38:39.010 --> 38:41.450
Bye.

38:41.450 --> 38:44.550
[♪]

38:57.460 --> 38:59.960
[♪]

39:14.910 --> 39:17.580
[♪]

39:20.050 --> 39:21.620
Ah, it's total b.S.

39:21.620 --> 39:23.660
You'd think we were
criminals or something.

39:23.660 --> 39:26.360
That mean we have to
ask permission to pee?

39:26.360 --> 39:27.990
Hell, they're already
all up in our business.

39:27.990 --> 39:29.360
Next thing you know,

39:29.360 --> 39:30.500
There won't be
any nooks or crannies

39:30.500 --> 39:32.130
To sneak a smoke
or whatnot.

39:32.130 --> 39:34.130
What are you
talking about?

39:34.130 --> 39:35.530
While you were
in the lock,

39:35.540 --> 39:37.470
We got ourselves a new
prison commissioner.

39:37.470 --> 39:38.800
A real hard-ass.

39:38.810 --> 39:41.970
He's adding "movement
accountability" protocols--

39:41.980 --> 39:43.140
Cameras everywhere,

39:43.140 --> 39:45.640
I.D. Badges, more rules.

39:45.650 --> 39:48.410
Shoot. We aren't
in our cells or at chow,

39:48.420 --> 39:50.620
We gotta present
special passes.

39:50.620 --> 39:53.450
It's all about
bein' "the man."

39:53.450 --> 39:54.890
When's this happening?

39:54.890 --> 39:56.720
Next week.

39:59.930 --> 40:02.860
I only got
about 10 minutes.

40:02.860 --> 40:05.430
Gonna tell me about
the new security?

40:06.930 --> 40:08.600
I was.

40:08.600 --> 40:10.840
I'm sorry.
I'm disappointed, too.

40:10.840 --> 40:12.570
You're disappointed?

40:12.570 --> 40:14.940
We missed our chance.

40:14.940 --> 40:16.170
The window's gonna close.

40:16.180 --> 40:18.040
You've just gotta
file another appeal.

40:18.040 --> 40:20.510
There are
no more appeals!

40:20.510 --> 40:21.910
[sighing]

40:21.920 --> 40:24.520
Look, we talked about
what was gonna happen

40:24.520 --> 40:25.950
If I lost my appeal.

40:25.950 --> 40:27.550
It's too late.

40:27.550 --> 40:28.950
You told me
you've never met

40:28.960 --> 40:31.190
Anyone who understood
you the way I do,

40:31.190 --> 40:33.430
Who makes you feel
the way I do,

40:33.430 --> 40:35.060
But when I really
need you...

40:35.060 --> 40:37.030
Whoa.

40:40.430 --> 40:43.000
[♪]

40:45.540 --> 40:47.210
There's a door off the gym
that isn't alarmed.

40:47.210 --> 40:48.610
I checked.

40:48.610 --> 40:50.510
It leads to the release area.

40:50.510 --> 40:52.810
From there, I've got
everything figured out.

40:52.810 --> 40:54.780
I'm not gonna grow old
in this prison

40:54.780 --> 40:56.050
For something
I didn't do.

40:56.050 --> 40:57.480
[jamie]: Don't do
anything stupid, sarah.

40:57.480 --> 40:58.820
We'll get through this.

40:58.820 --> 41:02.120
"we?" just get everything
together on that list,

41:02.120 --> 41:03.090
And be ready.

41:08.660 --> 41:10.560
Oh, that's perfect.

41:13.230 --> 41:16.000
He give this to you?

41:16.000 --> 41:18.000
Yeah.

41:21.640 --> 41:22.910
What if they shoot you?

41:22.910 --> 41:24.880
At least I'll be
wearing cute clothes.

41:24.880 --> 41:27.050
Oh, shut up.

41:27.050 --> 41:28.480
Come here.

41:28.480 --> 41:31.120
[♪]

41:45.100 --> 41:47.130
[♪]

41:48.270 --> 41:50.000
[corinne snaps]:
What'd I tell you?

41:50.000 --> 41:51.970
Huh? I told you not to--

41:51.970 --> 41:53.200
You didn't hear--

41:53.210 --> 41:55.540
[commotion continues]

42:01.110 --> 42:03.880
[strains of commotion carrying]

42:05.250 --> 42:08.620
[♪]

42:36.080 --> 42:38.220
[♪]

42:38.220 --> 42:41.920
[text alert vibrating]

42:41.920 --> 42:43.120
[sighs]

42:48.660 --> 42:51.060
[sighs shakily]

42:54.130 --> 42:56.800
[basketball dribbling
echoes in hall]

43:04.110 --> 43:06.780
[♪]

43:08.880 --> 43:10.680
[sighing]

43:10.680 --> 43:13.620
[text alert vibrating]

43:15.220 --> 43:18.020
[♪]

43:32.040 --> 43:34.870
[♪]

43:50.660 --> 43:53.760
[♪]

44:02.270 --> 44:04.000
[p.A.]: Visiting hours
are now over.

44:04.000 --> 44:05.800
All visitors
will have to report

44:05.810 --> 44:07.970
To the office to sign out.

44:23.790 --> 44:25.960
Pulling up to the gate.

44:25.960 --> 44:27.290
-The gate's open--
-scott!

44:27.290 --> 44:28.790
Stop the play-by-play!

44:30.130 --> 44:33.100
[♪]

44:36.240 --> 44:38.200
[brake engages]

44:39.710 --> 44:41.170
You kidding?

44:41.170 --> 44:43.210
I just needed to gas up
before I park it for the day.

44:43.210 --> 44:45.180
Take it easy, spitler.

44:50.280 --> 44:52.150
Just make it fast, huh?

44:54.850 --> 44:57.260
[♪]

45:02.900 --> 45:05.000
[guard slaps doors]

45:06.470 --> 45:09.270
[♪]

45:22.250 --> 45:25.820
[♪]

45:39.060 --> 45:41.500
When am I going
to see you again?

45:41.500 --> 45:43.940
Soon as it's safe,
I'll call you.

45:43.940 --> 45:46.100
We can finally
be together.

45:46.110 --> 45:48.140
[♪]

45:58.380 --> 46:00.890
[♪]

46:02.820 --> 46:04.520
Oh, my god!

46:04.520 --> 46:07.790
-We got to get outta here!
-Whoa!

46:18.040 --> 46:19.040
I'm done.

46:19.040 --> 46:20.170
[crunching paper]

46:20.170 --> 46:22.310
23 hours.

46:22.310 --> 46:24.110
Must be
some kind of record.

46:24.110 --> 46:25.440
Didn't even get
the sheets dirty.

46:25.450 --> 46:29.550
Of course, half the credit
goes to my co-star.

46:29.550 --> 46:31.120
This genius breaks
out of a maxi

46:31.120 --> 46:32.550
Outside of dayton,

46:32.550 --> 46:35.450
And then takes a bus to
his baby's mama's house in gary.

46:35.460 --> 46:37.920
I was waitin' for him
when he walked in.

46:37.920 --> 46:40.290
[chuckles]
sometimes, it's just too easy.

46:40.290 --> 46:42.460
[cell phone rings]

46:43.860 --> 46:45.800
Marshal harlan.

46:47.570 --> 46:49.300
I'm on my way.

46:49.300 --> 46:51.340
Start the clock, mccorkle.

46:51.340 --> 46:53.170
Woman just skipped out
of rockville.

46:53.170 --> 46:55.210
[jamie]: So you're gonna
be safe here, okay?

46:55.210 --> 46:56.510
It's an old foreclosure

46:56.510 --> 46:58.080
That me and ben were cleaning up
for the bank.

46:58.080 --> 47:00.980
I think you could probably
stay safe here for a week.

47:00.980 --> 47:02.280
Maybe even two.

47:02.280 --> 47:03.480
This is great.

47:03.480 --> 47:04.580
We got to cut
and color my hair.

47:04.580 --> 47:07.050
I cannot believe
you're standing here.

47:07.050 --> 47:08.090
Whoa.

47:08.090 --> 47:10.050
Where's all my stuff?

47:10.060 --> 47:12.220
Um, I have go pick it up.

47:12.230 --> 47:13.490
I don't know, I mean,

47:13.490 --> 47:15.590
I figured I'd have to go
on a food run anyway.

47:15.600 --> 47:17.430
I told you
to get everything ready.

47:17.430 --> 47:19.330
Yeah, but look,
you got out so fast.

47:19.330 --> 47:21.170
Well, can I get my money?

47:21.170 --> 47:23.500
Honey...

47:23.500 --> 47:26.400
Your money is temporarily
unavailable right now.

47:26.410 --> 47:28.470
No, no, no,
don't worry, we promise,

47:28.470 --> 47:30.110
We're gonna pay it back,
with interest.

47:30.110 --> 47:31.240
What did you do with my money?

47:31.240 --> 47:33.610
Ben always wanted a jacuzzi.

47:33.610 --> 47:36.350
You--! You used my money
to buy a hot tub?

47:36.350 --> 47:37.620
He has a bad back.

47:37.620 --> 47:39.550
Ohh! You said
you'd never let me down.

47:39.550 --> 47:42.190
Here, here, here.
Look, look, look, look, look.

47:43.620 --> 47:45.320
This is $33!

47:45.330 --> 47:46.860
[sighs] I'm gonna go

47:46.860 --> 47:50.460
And I'm gonna pick up
everything I can for you.

47:50.460 --> 47:51.260
Okay?

47:51.260 --> 47:53.130
Okay? I love you.

47:53.130 --> 47:55.200
Like warm,
fuzzy kittens.

47:57.140 --> 47:59.900
[fuming sigh]

48:01.010 --> 48:02.340
So between 2:30 and 4:00,

48:02.340 --> 48:04.210
You recorded
that three prison vehicles

48:04.210 --> 48:05.880
Exited the sally port?

48:05.880 --> 48:07.980
Two of the exiting vans
had offenders

48:07.980 --> 48:09.480
Who were being released
and transported

48:09.480 --> 48:11.350
To the greyhound station
downtown,

48:11.350 --> 48:13.450
But this third vehicle...

48:13.450 --> 48:16.020
[piqued]: Had a driver only?

48:16.020 --> 48:17.220
According to your notes,

48:17.220 --> 48:20.160
Transpo officer spitler...

48:20.160 --> 48:21.960
Needed to refuel.

48:21.960 --> 48:23.960
How well do you know spitler?

48:25.500 --> 48:28.330
Scott spitler
has worked here for five years,

48:28.330 --> 48:29.570
Marshal harlan.

48:29.570 --> 48:31.540
He's married,
with two small kids.

48:36.140 --> 48:39.080
I glanced inside,

48:39.080 --> 48:40.280
But spitler
was in a hurry.

48:40.280 --> 48:41.410
He's a model guard.

48:41.410 --> 48:43.980
He ain't perfect, ms. Rogers.

48:45.020 --> 48:45.980
There've been rumors.

48:45.990 --> 48:48.320
What kind of rumors?

48:49.320 --> 48:51.920
Soap and water
weren't the only fluids

48:51.930 --> 48:53.960
They've been mixing
in the chemical closet.

48:56.090 --> 48:58.100
This is bull!

48:58.100 --> 48:59.600
I'm the straightest arrow here.

48:59.600 --> 49:00.930
Why did you rush
the van inspection

49:00.930 --> 49:02.470
When you exited
after refueling?

49:02.470 --> 49:03.530
Check your records,
marshal.

49:03.540 --> 49:05.470
Since I've been
a trip officer,

49:05.470 --> 49:07.470
I've never skipped
van inspection.

49:07.470 --> 49:09.340
I get it.

49:09.340 --> 49:11.640
You're not the kind of
guy who flaunts rules.

49:12.580 --> 49:15.710
Let's talk about
the chemical closet.

49:15.720 --> 49:18.620
You say you barely
knew sarah pender,

49:18.620 --> 49:20.180
But according
to prison records,

49:20.190 --> 49:22.090
You were her supervisor

49:22.090 --> 49:24.360
When she was
on chemical duty.

49:24.360 --> 49:27.090
I supervised a lot of women
on chemical duty.

49:28.960 --> 49:31.000
I did not do anything wrong
with that woman.

49:32.000 --> 49:33.360
She had help
on the inside, scott.

49:33.370 --> 49:35.100
We have to ask everyone.

49:35.100 --> 49:38.200
I know.

49:38.200 --> 49:40.000
So, officer spitler.

49:40.010 --> 49:42.970
You didn't do anything
wrong with that woman?

49:42.980 --> 49:45.240
No. I did not.

49:45.240 --> 49:48.280
Did you know,
when people lie,

49:48.280 --> 49:49.650
They don't use
contractions?

49:49.650 --> 49:53.350
And they use distancing phrases
like "that woman"

49:53.350 --> 49:55.720
When they really meant
"monica lewinski."

49:57.220 --> 49:59.490
You're lying.

50:01.160 --> 50:03.130
[♪]

50:06.400 --> 50:08.170
I'm sorry, ms. Rogers.

50:08.170 --> 50:10.740
Scott?

50:10.740 --> 50:12.670
Is this true?

50:14.270 --> 50:16.110
What the hell
were you thinking?

50:17.280 --> 50:19.140
I don't know.

50:19.150 --> 50:22.150
I was...

50:22.150 --> 50:23.480
It just made sense.

50:25.450 --> 50:28.320
Sarah, she understood me.

50:28.320 --> 50:30.020
She...

50:30.020 --> 50:31.690
Loved me.

50:31.690 --> 50:34.190
She wanted to have my baby.

50:34.190 --> 50:36.130
Where is she?

50:36.130 --> 50:38.200
I don't know.

50:38.200 --> 50:40.630
I swear.

50:42.400 --> 50:45.040
Sarah didn't tell me anything.

50:46.070 --> 50:47.340
My job

50:47.340 --> 50:49.140
Was just to get her
to the parking lot.

50:51.810 --> 50:53.140
[answering machine beeps]

50:53.150 --> 50:54.580
Daddy. I'm out.

50:54.580 --> 50:56.280
Please don't be mad at me.

50:56.280 --> 50:59.650
I tried it their way,
but they gave me no choice.

50:59.650 --> 51:01.190
I'll be in touch
when I can.

51:01.190 --> 51:02.450
I love you.

51:02.460 --> 51:04.460
[♪]

51:06.460 --> 51:08.630
I need a list of
all the women in the area

51:08.630 --> 51:10.060
Who did time with pender.

51:10.060 --> 51:12.560
That'll be
a long list.

51:12.570 --> 51:16.130
[♪]

51:31.680 --> 51:33.580
I want to speak to her.

51:33.590 --> 51:35.790
[ben]: Told you
this was gonna end bad.

51:35.790 --> 51:37.720
Said the fat man
in the hot tub.

51:37.720 --> 51:40.090
Ah, shut it.

51:40.090 --> 51:41.790
She's gonna kill me.

51:41.790 --> 51:44.100
[doorbell chimes]

51:44.100 --> 51:45.830
[knocking at door]

51:47.330 --> 51:48.630
Jamie long?
Open the door!

51:48.630 --> 51:50.530
U.S. Marshal sean harlan.

51:50.540 --> 51:52.600
Open the door!

51:56.140 --> 51:58.440
How can I help you?

51:59.380 --> 52:01.650
I'm looking for sarah pender.

52:01.650 --> 52:03.750
Well, have you tried
rockville prison?

52:03.750 --> 52:06.420
[snickers dryly]
is anyone else in the house?

52:06.420 --> 52:09.220
Oh. Yeah. Uh, ben's...

52:09.220 --> 52:11.390
Out back in the jacuzzi.

52:11.390 --> 52:13.420
But you don't want to
see that.

52:13.430 --> 52:16.730
You're not curious
why I'm looking for her?

52:16.730 --> 52:19.430
Oh, I guess
that she's probably missing.

52:19.430 --> 52:20.660
Good guess.

52:20.670 --> 52:22.770
The guard
that helped pender escape

52:22.770 --> 52:24.540
Said you drove
the getaway car.

52:24.540 --> 52:25.640
He didn't see me.

52:25.640 --> 52:29.370
No, he didn't. I lied.

52:29.380 --> 52:30.810
Jamie, where is she?

52:30.810 --> 52:33.840
Sarah didn't kill
those people!

52:33.850 --> 52:36.610
She's a fugitive now,
with a target on her back.

52:36.620 --> 52:38.180
But I can bring her in alive.

52:38.180 --> 52:40.150
You don't give a rat's ass about
sarah.

52:40.150 --> 52:43.890
She's got nothing to lose.
You have everything.

52:43.890 --> 52:46.490
Aiding and abetting
an escaped prisoner is a felony.

52:46.490 --> 52:47.790
You've already done the crime.

52:47.790 --> 52:50.560
You can't help her
anymore.

52:50.560 --> 52:52.330
You can only
help yourself.

52:52.330 --> 52:54.400
Jamie!

52:54.400 --> 52:56.230
You tell the man
where she is,

52:56.240 --> 52:58.340
Or I will.

52:58.340 --> 53:00.910
[♪]

53:17.660 --> 53:20.660
[♪]

53:37.440 --> 53:40.340
[♪]

53:41.980 --> 53:43.880
