speak with her now?

01:07:07.690 --> 01:07:11.150
Run, sarah. Run.

01:07:11.160 --> 01:07:13.520
Officially added
to the u.S. Marshal's

01:07:13.530 --> 01:07:14.690
Top 15,

01:07:14.690 --> 01:07:17.030
The only woman on that list.

01:07:17.030 --> 01:07:18.730
Well, how 'bout that?

01:07:18.730 --> 01:07:20.200
What do you think of sarah?

01:07:20.200 --> 01:07:21.500
Bobby hopner couldn't
get a cheerleader

01:07:21.500 --> 01:07:23.200
To give him
the time of day.

01:07:23.200 --> 01:07:24.400
And now...

01:07:24.400 --> 01:07:27.170
I'm sleeping with
america's most wanted woman.

01:07:27.170 --> 01:07:30.740
She is a convicted murderer.
She knows how to use people.

01:07:30.740 --> 01:07:34.740
She gets ordinary people
to do horrible things,

01:07:34.750 --> 01:07:36.480
And then she flushes them
down the toilet,

01:07:36.480 --> 01:07:38.420
Just like she flushed
those two bodies

01:07:38.420 --> 01:07:40.350
In the dumpster.

01:07:40.350 --> 01:07:41.820
So...

01:07:41.820 --> 01:07:44.090
Do you think
I'm ordinary, baby?

01:07:44.090 --> 01:07:46.420
You're not
that special.

01:07:46.430 --> 01:07:47.460
Oh, really?

01:07:47.460 --> 01:07:48.630
Just sayin'.

01:07:48.630 --> 01:07:50.560
For u.S. Marshal sean harlan,

01:07:50.560 --> 01:07:53.300
Bringing in pender
is his top priority,

01:07:53.300 --> 01:07:55.600
And one he takes
very personally.

01:07:55.600 --> 01:07:56.800
You're gonna make a mistake.

01:07:56.800 --> 01:07:59.500
When you do,

01:07:59.500 --> 01:08:02.070
I'm gonna catch you.

01:08:02.070 --> 01:08:04.110
[walsh]: So if you've seen sarah
pender,

01:08:04.110 --> 01:08:05.840
Call us at 1-800-crime-tv.

01:08:05.840 --> 01:08:08.510
[♪]

01:08:13.520 --> 01:08:15.690
[♪]

01:08:15.690 --> 01:08:19.760
I'll call on this phone
when I can.

01:08:19.760 --> 01:08:22.290
[♪]

01:08:30.700 --> 01:08:32.370
So what do you
think of bali?

01:08:32.370 --> 01:08:33.870
Well, it says here
you can get

01:08:33.870 --> 01:08:35.870
A better cup of coffee there
than you can in rome.

01:08:35.870 --> 01:08:37.640
And they have
no extradition treaty

01:08:37.640 --> 01:08:38.740
With the u.S.

01:08:38.740 --> 01:08:41.479
We deserve to be happy.

01:08:41.479 --> 01:08:43.510
I'm happy now.

01:08:43.520 --> 01:08:45.880
Hey, did jerry tell you
about the mistake I found

01:08:45.880 --> 01:08:47.319
In his bookkeeping?

01:08:47.319 --> 01:08:48.750
What mistake?

01:08:48.750 --> 01:08:50.250
50% of
your payroll tax remittance

01:08:50.260 --> 01:08:52.319
Is money withheld
from employee pay,

01:08:52.319 --> 01:08:54.520
Which are wage expenses,
not payroll.

01:08:54.529 --> 01:08:57.189
Jerry's been writing them off
as payroll expenses.

01:08:57.200 --> 01:08:58.160
Crap.

01:08:58.160 --> 01:08:59.330
Don't worry, honey.

01:08:59.330 --> 01:09:00.500
I showed jerry
his mistake.

01:09:00.500 --> 01:09:02.200
As long as you pay
the back taxes,

01:09:02.200 --> 01:09:04.569
You won't be audited.

01:09:04.569 --> 01:09:07.600
Let me do the books
at all your warehouses.

01:09:07.609 --> 01:09:10.240
My wife sits on my board.

01:09:10.240 --> 01:09:12.180
If she finds out about us,

01:09:12.180 --> 01:09:13.710
It could cause me
a lot of problems.

01:09:13.710 --> 01:09:18.850
Hey. Why do we have to
upset this special thing, huh?

01:09:18.850 --> 01:09:20.250
I love what we have,

01:09:20.250 --> 01:09:21.580
But I'm a hunted woman,

01:09:21.590 --> 01:09:23.450
And you're aiding and abetting
a fugitive.

01:09:23.460 --> 01:09:25.890
It would be in
both of our interests

01:09:25.890 --> 01:09:27.520
To get a plan together,

01:09:27.529 --> 01:09:28.930
A long-term plan,

01:09:28.930 --> 01:09:32.399
Otherwise we're just playing
a dangerous game of "house."

01:09:34.170 --> 01:09:37.200
[♪]

01:09:39.470 --> 01:09:41.399
[♪]

01:09:44.740 --> 01:09:47.710
What is it, jer?

01:09:47.710 --> 01:09:48.750
I'm a little busy.

01:09:48.750 --> 01:09:49.950
Bob told me about

01:09:49.950 --> 01:09:52.180
The accounting mistake
you found.

01:09:52.180 --> 01:09:55.650
I've been doing
a little snooping on my own.

01:09:55.650 --> 01:09:58.760
Bob's wife doesn't have
a cousin named "ashley."

01:09:58.760 --> 01:10:01.690
Maybe... Maybe we should
give her a call.

01:10:01.690 --> 01:10:03.630
Why don't we?

01:10:04.730 --> 01:10:05.900
As a member of the board,

01:10:05.900 --> 01:10:07.500
I'm sure
she'd be interested to learn

01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:09.800
How you've been
ripping this company off blind.

01:10:09.800 --> 01:10:11.800
And I'm not talking
your incompetence,

01:10:11.800 --> 01:10:13.940
I'm talking straight-up
embezzlement.

01:10:13.940 --> 01:10:15.440
Imagine my surprise

01:10:15.440 --> 01:10:17.540
When I called that glue vendor
up in fort wayne

01:10:17.540 --> 01:10:19.240
About a check
that never cleared,

01:10:19.240 --> 01:10:22.310
Found out they've been
out of business for three years.

01:10:22.310 --> 01:10:25.680
Any idea who's been
forging their signature?

01:10:25.680 --> 01:10:27.950
Or where
that 38-grand went to?

01:10:27.950 --> 01:10:30.650
So what do you think, jerry?

01:10:30.660 --> 01:10:33.420
Should we call?

01:10:33.430 --> 01:10:35.990
[♪]

01:10:38.960 --> 01:10:41.930
I wasn't gonna
call the police, but...

01:10:41.930 --> 01:10:44.500
When I saw
america's most wanted...

01:10:44.500 --> 01:10:46.500
[sighs]:
I don't want her to get hurt.

01:10:46.500 --> 01:10:49.270
I can't imagine
how difficult this must be

01:10:49.270 --> 01:10:50.510
For you as a father.

01:10:50.510 --> 01:10:52.810
She was only three
when her mom left,

01:10:52.810 --> 01:10:54.680
Just took off.

01:10:54.680 --> 01:10:56.680
I went and got her,

01:10:56.680 --> 01:10:59.450
Brought her here
and raised her.

01:10:59.450 --> 01:11:02.250
I guess I probably spoiled her.

01:11:02.250 --> 01:11:05.020
She got me
to do whatever she wanted.

01:11:05.020 --> 01:11:09.290
She never liked
the word, "no."

01:11:09.290 --> 01:11:13.630
I just... I just wanted her
to feel loved.

01:11:13.630 --> 01:11:15.800
She always wanted more.

01:11:15.800 --> 01:11:17.900
[sighs]

01:11:19.470 --> 01:11:21.340
Is sarah capable

01:11:21.340 --> 01:11:24.440
Of doing the things
she was convicted of?

01:11:27.950 --> 01:11:31.310
When it comes to surviving...

01:11:33.420 --> 01:11:38.050
My daughter is capable of
doing anything.

01:11:39.620 --> 01:11:41.660
[sighs wearily]

01:11:48.000 --> 01:11:51.470
[♪]

01:12:00.480 --> 01:12:03.880
[phone rings]

01:12:08.750 --> 01:12:10.720
Daddy?

01:12:11.960 --> 01:12:13.090
Who is this?

01:12:13.090 --> 01:12:15.090
U.S. Marshal harlan.

01:12:15.090 --> 01:12:16.860
Don't hang up.

01:12:16.860 --> 01:12:18.560
How did you get this phone?

01:12:18.560 --> 01:12:19.530
Your dad.

01:12:19.530 --> 01:12:21.530
He has nothing
to do with this.

01:12:21.530 --> 01:12:22.970
You dragged him into it
when you sent him the phone.

01:12:22.970 --> 01:12:24.370
That's why he called me.

01:12:24.370 --> 01:12:25.970
-He called you?
-Yeah.

01:12:25.970 --> 01:12:27.500
Real nice man.

01:12:27.510 --> 01:12:29.010
Leave my father alone!

01:12:29.010 --> 01:12:30.410
You're killing him, sarah.

01:12:30.410 --> 01:12:32.510
Shut up! Shut up.

01:12:32.510 --> 01:12:34.980
Tell me where you are.

01:12:34.980 --> 01:12:38.450
I'll bring you in.
Do it for your father.

01:12:38.450 --> 01:12:40.020
Must be frustrating,
marshal harlan.

01:12:40.020 --> 01:12:41.480
You got pretty close to me

01:12:41.490 --> 01:12:43.120
At that motel,
but ever since then,

01:12:43.120 --> 01:12:47.460
[sighs] whoever's helping you,
they know you're a killer.

01:12:47.460 --> 01:12:48.660
I'm not a killer!

01:12:48.660 --> 01:12:49.930
So your two roommates
shot themselves?

01:12:49.930 --> 01:12:51.490
Rick is an idiot!
If I wanted to kill someone,

01:12:51.500 --> 01:12:52.960
I wouldn't have shot them
in my living room

01:12:52.960 --> 01:12:54.730
And dumped their bodies
around the corner.

01:12:54.730 --> 01:12:55.870
Then why didn't you
call the cops?

01:12:55.870 --> 01:12:58.530
I just saw my boyfriend
kill drew.

01:13:00.140 --> 01:13:02.140
Yeah. That would scare anyone.

01:13:02.140 --> 01:13:03.570
I get it.

01:13:03.580 --> 01:13:05.070
You saw your boyfriend
shoot drew,

01:13:05.080 --> 01:13:06.610
Then you saw him shoot--

01:13:06.610 --> 01:13:07.910
What was her name?

01:13:07.910 --> 01:13:09.880
I didn't see rick shoot trish. I
wasn't there.

01:13:09.880 --> 01:13:10.880
You just said--

01:13:10.880 --> 01:13:11.880
[snap]

01:13:11.880 --> 01:13:14.450
[fuming]

01:13:14.450 --> 01:13:15.890
They got a weak hit

01:13:15.890 --> 01:13:17.720
On two towers off I-80,
between gary and toledo.

01:13:17.720 --> 01:13:19.060
She's been in
the midwest

01:13:19.060 --> 01:13:19.990
The whole time.

01:13:19.990 --> 01:13:21.690
Get on it.

01:13:21.690 --> 01:13:23.060
Pender just let it slip that
she saw her boyfriend kill drew.

01:13:23.060 --> 01:13:24.690
She's always claimed

01:13:24.700 --> 01:13:25.630
She wasn't in the house
when the killings occurred.

01:13:25.630 --> 01:13:26.860
Well, does it really matter?

01:13:26.870 --> 01:13:29.600
It's the first slip-up
she's made.

01:13:29.600 --> 01:13:32.100
When she does it again,
I'm gonna be there.

01:13:32.100 --> 01:13:34.770
[♪]

01:13:36.040 --> 01:13:39.010
[cell phone ringing]

01:13:41.750 --> 01:13:42.580
[gasps]

01:13:42.580 --> 01:13:43.980
She's right here.

01:13:45.080 --> 01:13:47.180
Gotcha.

01:13:47.190 --> 01:13:48.520
[cell phone ringing]

01:13:50.620 --> 01:13:52.590
[ragged breathing]

01:13:52.590 --> 01:13:54.660
[phone continues to ring]

01:13:57.660 --> 01:13:59.460
Where have you been?
I've been calling you all night.

01:13:59.460 --> 01:14:00.800
-Hey, what's wrong?
-Everything!

01:14:00.800 --> 01:14:02.800
That u.S. Marshal's
gotten to my dad.

01:14:02.800 --> 01:14:03.670
Jerry knows
I'm not your cousin.

01:14:03.670 --> 01:14:04.800
I'll handle jerry.

01:14:04.800 --> 01:14:07.100
All this hiding
and pretending.

01:14:07.110 --> 01:14:08.570
I need to find

01:14:08.570 --> 01:14:10.210
Someone who can commit
to a future with me.

01:14:10.210 --> 01:14:12.440
Listen. I'm that guy.

01:14:12.440 --> 01:14:13.540
Okay?

01:14:13.550 --> 01:14:15.010
We'll start over.

01:14:15.010 --> 01:14:16.910
I'm gonna make you happy, sarah.

01:14:16.920 --> 01:14:19.080
I promise.

01:14:19.080 --> 01:14:20.580
[bob]: Wait.

01:14:20.590 --> 01:14:21.920
[sarah]: Where are we?

01:14:21.920 --> 01:14:22.890
Keep them closed.

01:14:22.890 --> 01:14:23.890
Okay...

01:14:23.890 --> 01:14:25.020
Okay.
You can open 'em.

01:14:27.220 --> 01:14:29.230
You like?

01:14:29.230 --> 01:14:30.960
I rented it for you.

01:14:30.960 --> 01:14:32.090
For us.

01:14:32.100 --> 01:14:34.060
This is amazing.

01:14:34.070 --> 01:14:35.900
I love it.

01:14:35.900 --> 01:14:38.000
I love you.

01:14:39.140 --> 01:14:42.840
You want to go upstairs?

01:14:42.840 --> 01:14:44.740
I... I can't.

01:14:44.740 --> 01:14:47.010
Betty's expecting me
for dinner.

01:14:47.010 --> 01:14:48.640
[groans quietly]

01:14:48.650 --> 01:14:51.250
We've got to start
implementing our plan, bob.

01:14:51.250 --> 01:14:52.650
You can't have
everything you want.

01:14:52.650 --> 01:14:53.780
You've got to make choices.

01:14:53.790 --> 01:14:56.090
Sarah, I can't
marry a fugitive.

01:14:56.090 --> 01:14:58.250
You can't marry anyone
until you get a divorce.

01:14:58.260 --> 01:14:59.920
Divorces are complicated.

01:14:59.920 --> 01:15:02.790
Betty could take me
for millions.

01:15:02.790 --> 01:15:06.030
Maybe there's
a simpler solution.

01:15:08.270 --> 01:15:10.830
I know what I want.

01:15:10.840 --> 01:15:13.200
And I want to be
the next mrs. Robert hopner,

01:15:13.200 --> 01:15:16.170
But I'm not gonna wait forever
for you to decide.

01:15:16.170 --> 01:15:19.580
[♪]

01:15:25.020 --> 01:15:27.280
[inhales and sighs]
sorry, marshal.

01:15:27.290 --> 01:15:29.150
I have no idea where she'd go.

01:15:29.150 --> 01:15:30.650
After three months on the run,

01:15:30.660 --> 01:15:32.760
I'm not holding my breath
for a call, either.

01:15:32.760 --> 01:15:34.590
She's been out
four months.

01:15:34.590 --> 01:15:37.630
133 days,
but who's counting?

01:15:37.630 --> 01:15:40.200
The only time sarah
ever communicated with me

01:15:40.200 --> 01:15:41.560
Since we were arrested

01:15:41.570 --> 01:15:44.930
Was when she needed
an affidavit.

01:15:44.940 --> 01:15:48.800
She blames that forged letter
in getting her 110 years.

01:15:48.810 --> 01:15:51.310
I was just trying to
save my own ass from the needle.

01:15:51.310 --> 01:15:53.040
The prosecution
used it

01:15:53.040 --> 01:15:54.640
To turn sarah
into the boogeyman.

01:15:54.650 --> 01:15:57.080
Otherwise, she might've
gotten away with it.

01:15:57.080 --> 01:15:59.580
Gotten away with what?

01:16:02.190 --> 01:16:05.620
Her role in it.

01:16:08.260 --> 01:16:09.890
Ease up.

01:16:09.890 --> 01:16:11.990
Those things'll
kill you.

01:16:12.000 --> 01:16:13.300
Not soon enough.

01:16:13.300 --> 01:16:15.870
[takes a tense breath]

01:16:15.870 --> 01:16:19.140
You know, I was happy
with what we had...

01:16:19.140 --> 01:16:20.800
But sarah always wanted more.

01:16:20.810 --> 01:16:23.210
Fancy cars? Jewelry?

01:16:23.210 --> 01:16:25.210
[snorts]
sarah? You kidding?

01:16:25.210 --> 01:16:28.180
Nah, she wanted a family.

01:16:28.180 --> 01:16:29.980
A big family.

01:16:29.980 --> 01:16:32.850
Six or seven kids.

01:16:32.850 --> 01:16:34.650
It was all about the kids
for her.

01:16:34.650 --> 01:16:36.150
She wanted to give them

01:16:36.150 --> 01:16:38.050
The childhood
she didn't get to have.

01:16:40.960 --> 01:16:43.890
Doesn't fit the picture
of sarah in your mind?

01:16:45.230 --> 01:16:47.160
Guard.

01:16:55.340 --> 01:16:58.940
So a.M.W. 's going to lead
with a pender update.

01:16:58.940 --> 01:17:00.310
What's up?

01:17:00.310 --> 01:17:01.640
Call rockville.

01:17:01.650 --> 01:17:03.250
Find out if anyone
in pender's orbit

01:17:03.250 --> 01:17:04.680
Had three daughters.

01:17:04.680 --> 01:17:07.180
These kids
are very important to her.

01:17:07.190 --> 01:17:09.190
Who are they?

01:17:09.190 --> 01:17:12.150
[♪]

01:17:18.000 --> 01:17:19.200
Hey, baby.

01:17:19.200 --> 01:17:20.400
Hi.

01:17:20.400 --> 01:17:22.160
So I talked to
a plastic surgeon

01:17:22.170 --> 01:17:23.370
Today, in new york.

01:17:23.370 --> 01:17:25.130
He can do everything
for about 13 grand--

01:17:25.140 --> 01:17:27.400
Nose, cheek-lifts, chin.

01:17:27.410 --> 01:17:29.170
A whole new me,
in eight hours.

01:17:29.170 --> 01:17:30.810
Great.

01:17:30.810 --> 01:17:32.740
We could stay a few extra days.

01:17:32.740 --> 01:17:35.080
We can make
a little honeymoon out of it.

01:17:35.080 --> 01:17:38.780
I can't wait to have
a normal life with you.

01:17:40.020 --> 01:17:41.250
Me too.

01:17:41.250 --> 01:17:43.690
[♪]

01:17:43.690 --> 01:17:45.020
[she resumes typing]

01:17:45.020 --> 01:17:45.990
[♪]

01:17:45.990 --> 01:17:47.320
[mccorkle]:
Farrell loman.

01:17:47.330 --> 01:17:49.160
Who is she?

01:17:49.160 --> 01:17:50.760
A stripper.

01:17:50.760 --> 01:17:52.760
She did a nine-month bid
for solicitation.

01:17:52.760 --> 01:17:54.900
Sarah helped her
keep her kids.

01:17:54.900 --> 01:17:56.230
I don't remember the name.

01:17:56.230 --> 01:17:58.300
She's not on sarah's call
or visitation list,

01:17:58.300 --> 01:17:59.370
So we missed her.

01:17:59.370 --> 01:18:03.070
Oh! Look at
the pink cupcakes!

01:18:03.070 --> 01:18:05.340
Just for my baby.

01:18:05.340 --> 01:18:07.440
You like your pink
cupcakes, baby girl?

01:18:07.450 --> 01:18:09.680
Yeah?

01:18:09.680 --> 01:18:11.180
[truck rumbling]

01:18:11.180 --> 01:18:13.150
Okay, I'll be right back.

01:18:15.720 --> 01:18:17.850
[♪]

01:18:20.120 --> 01:18:22.160
Can I help you?

01:18:22.160 --> 01:18:23.760
That's a nice party.

01:18:23.760 --> 01:18:25.230
I've got
a five-year-old,

01:18:25.230 --> 01:18:26.400
But he's with
his mother

01:18:26.400 --> 01:18:28.200
In columbus.

01:18:28.200 --> 01:18:30.730
U.S. Marshal sean harlan.

01:18:30.740 --> 01:18:32.800
I'm looking for
sarah pender.

01:18:32.800 --> 01:18:35.200
I... I don't have any idea.

01:18:35.210 --> 01:18:37.770
I know she helped you
keep custody of your kids.

01:18:37.780 --> 01:18:39.710
It'd be a shame
to lose them now.

01:18:39.710 --> 01:18:42.950
To you,
I'm just some ex-con stripper,

01:18:42.950 --> 01:18:45.820
But to my girls,
I'm mom,

01:18:45.820 --> 01:18:47.380
And I owe that to sarah.

01:18:47.390 --> 01:18:48.920
She dragged you
into this,

01:18:48.920 --> 01:18:50.750
And she's putting you
and your kids at risk.

01:18:50.760 --> 01:18:52.350
She was desperate.

01:18:52.360 --> 01:18:54.760
Tell me where she is,

01:18:54.760 --> 01:18:57.030
And I'll keep you out of this,
I promise.

01:18:57.030 --> 01:18:58.430
Your parole officer
never has to know.

01:18:58.430 --> 01:19:01.160
Do it for
your daughters.

01:19:01.170 --> 01:19:03.300
[sighs tensely]

01:19:03.300 --> 01:19:05.370
[♪]

01:19:07.740 --> 01:19:10.370
[♪]

01:19:20.320 --> 01:19:22.820
[♪]

01:19:29.430 --> 01:19:31.260
When did you
get home?

01:19:31.260 --> 01:19:33.830
Dinner won't be ready
for awhile yet.

01:19:33.830 --> 01:19:37.300
Opened one of those
napa pinots you like.

01:19:38.400 --> 01:19:40.540
What's the occasion?

01:19:40.540 --> 01:19:44.170
We didn't used to need one.

01:20:03.930 --> 01:20:05.830
Bob hopner, right?

01:20:05.830 --> 01:20:08.060
Yeah. Hey.

01:20:08.070 --> 01:20:10.800
Hey, I know you.
How do I know you?

01:20:10.800 --> 01:20:12.200
Well, maybe
you saw me on tv.

01:20:12.200 --> 01:20:13.840
America's
most wanted?

01:20:13.840 --> 01:20:15.300
Sean harlan.
U.S. Marshals.

01:20:15.310 --> 01:20:17.270
Fugitive recovery
task force.

01:20:17.280 --> 01:20:18.110
Right.

01:20:18.110 --> 01:20:19.310
Where is she, bob?

01:20:19.310 --> 01:20:22.240
Who? I... I don't
know what you mean.

01:20:22.250 --> 01:20:25.410
I can handcuff you right now
and take you inside

01:20:25.420 --> 01:20:26.920
And do this
in front of your wife.

01:20:26.920 --> 01:20:28.250
My wife's not home.

01:20:28.250 --> 01:20:30.320
But that's betty's car
right there.

01:20:30.320 --> 01:20:32.390
I ran
the registration.

01:20:32.390 --> 01:20:35.120
So, should we
include mrs. Hopner

01:20:35.130 --> 01:20:36.430
In this conversation?

01:20:36.430 --> 01:20:38.360
Okay. Look.

01:20:40.600 --> 01:20:42.500
I spent one night
with sarah

01:20:42.500 --> 01:20:43.970
A few months ago.

01:20:43.970 --> 01:20:45.940
Okay?

01:20:45.940 --> 01:20:47.340
Look, I'm out
on the road a lot.

01:20:47.340 --> 01:20:50.070
I sometimes like to
party with women.

01:20:51.040 --> 01:20:52.170
I mean, that was it.

01:20:52.180 --> 01:20:53.880
It was a few months ago,

01:20:53.880 --> 01:20:55.040
And I haven't
seen her since.

01:20:55.050 --> 01:20:56.210
She didn't tell you
who she was,

01:20:56.210 --> 01:20:57.480
Or what she'd done?

01:20:57.480 --> 01:20:58.550
No.

01:20:58.550 --> 01:21:00.550
No, I mean,
I didn't realize,

01:21:00.550 --> 01:21:03.020
Until I saw her face
on that most wanted show.

01:21:03.020 --> 01:21:04.290
Why didn't you call the show?

01:21:04.290 --> 01:21:05.420
You could've collected
the reward.

01:21:05.420 --> 01:21:07.960
Yeah. Uh...

01:21:07.960 --> 01:21:10.590
I'm not sure how I would have
explained that one to the wife.

01:21:10.600 --> 01:21:12.490
Right.

01:21:12.500 --> 01:21:17.200
Most people who come
into contact with sarah pender

01:21:17.200 --> 01:21:18.230
And up dead
or in jail.

01:21:18.240 --> 01:21:21.240
Well, I make
my own luck, marshal.

01:21:21.240 --> 01:21:23.570
Thanks for your time, bob.

01:21:23.570 --> 01:21:26.240
[♪]

01:21:26.240 --> 01:21:28.240
The arrogant jackass.

01:21:28.250 --> 01:21:29.580
He knows where pender is.

01:21:29.580 --> 01:21:31.380
That's why I'm gonna let him
lead us to her.

01:21:31.380 --> 01:21:33.020
How many cell lines
does he have?

01:21:33.020 --> 01:21:34.220
He's got three.

01:21:34.220 --> 01:21:35.250
The first one
seems strictly business,

01:21:35.250 --> 01:21:37.120
Mainly 9:00-to-5:00,

01:21:37.120 --> 01:21:38.420
But the third one
never calls

01:21:38.420 --> 01:21:40.460
His home line
or his wife's cell.

01:21:40.460 --> 01:21:42.220
Lots of calls to muncie,
up until a month ago.

01:21:42.230 --> 01:21:44.490
The recent activity is
all in the chicago area.

01:21:44.500 --> 01:21:46.100
I'm going to chicago.

01:21:46.100 --> 01:21:48.200
Stay up on all his lines.

01:21:48.200 --> 01:21:50.570
[♪]

01:21:53.970 --> 01:21:54.940
Hey.

01:21:54.940 --> 01:21:56.670
You're on tv, right?

01:21:56.670 --> 01:21:59.310
One of them
reality shows?

01:21:59.310 --> 01:22:01.480
No. Sorry.

01:22:04.110 --> 01:22:06.180
[♪]

01:22:08.390 --> 01:22:10.650
Baby... You know how much
I love you, don't you?

01:22:10.660 --> 01:22:12.150
I know this hasn't been easy,

01:22:12.160 --> 01:22:14.420
But we're gonna finally
be happy together.

01:22:14.430 --> 01:22:17.260
I'm going to go get packed.
I'll see you tonight.

01:22:17.260 --> 01:22:19.300
Just call me
when you're on the way.

01:22:19.300 --> 01:22:22.160
[mccorkle]: The carrier
needs to see a warrant first.

01:22:22.170 --> 01:22:23.430
Mccorkle,
we've got a warrant!

01:22:23.430 --> 01:22:26.700
Fax it to them,
get me the damn number.

01:22:28.570 --> 01:22:33.580
On my personal top 10 fugitive
list of the year

01:22:33.580 --> 01:22:37.680
Currently the only woman
on that list.

01:22:37.680 --> 01:22:39.450
Pender's a double-murderer

01:22:39.450 --> 01:22:42.020
Who broke out of
rockville prison in indiana

01:22:42.020 --> 01:22:43.990
Several months ago.

01:22:43.990 --> 01:22:47.320
[phone rings]

01:22:48.390 --> 01:22:50.030
Bob?

01:22:50.030 --> 01:22:52.460
[silence]

01:22:57.100 --> 01:22:58.200
Get it?

01:22:58.200 --> 01:22:59.400
[mccorkle]: Got it.

01:22:59.400 --> 01:23:01.340
On clybourn
and fullerton.

01:23:01.340 --> 01:23:02.710
Puts her about

01:23:02.710 --> 01:23:04.410
Five miles southwest
of downtown chicago.

01:23:04.410 --> 01:23:05.740
Slip-up number two.
Where do I go?

01:23:05.740 --> 01:23:07.380
Take ashland north.

01:23:07.380 --> 01:23:10.480
Maybe I can put you
on a specific street.

01:23:10.480 --> 01:23:13.380
[♪]

01:23:16.320 --> 01:23:17.520
[knocking at door]

01:23:17.520 --> 01:23:19.120
Gas company.

01:23:19.120 --> 01:23:21.290
We need to do
a meter-reading.

01:23:24.190 --> 01:23:26.400
Sarah jo pender?

01:23:28.100 --> 01:23:29.500
You got me.

01:23:29.500 --> 01:23:32.170
Hands on your head.
Turn around.

01:23:33.600 --> 01:23:36.010
Where's marshal harlan?

01:23:36.010 --> 01:23:37.770
Who?

01:23:39.110 --> 01:23:42.310
[radios crackling,
quiet chatter]

01:23:50.420 --> 01:23:52.420
[sean]: U.S. Marshal.
Where is she?

01:23:52.420 --> 01:23:53.620
[officer]:
We're upstairs, sir.

01:23:56.560 --> 01:23:58.130
Marshal harlan.

01:23:58.130 --> 01:24:01.200
Too bad you didn't
catch me.

01:24:02.470 --> 01:24:06.100
Sometimes...
It takes a village.

01:24:06.100 --> 01:24:08.700
[♪]

01:24:12.810 --> 01:24:16.110
[tv reporter]:
Acting on an anonymous tip,

01:24:16.110 --> 01:24:18.380
U.S. Marshal
top 15 fugitive sarah pender,

01:24:18.380 --> 01:24:20.680
In a rented townhouse

01:24:20.680 --> 01:24:23.590
On the southwest side
of the city.

01:24:23.590 --> 01:24:26.360
The tipster,
who wouldn't leave a name,

01:24:26.360 --> 01:24:30.090
From an episode
of america's most wanted,

01:24:30.090 --> 01:24:31.760
Which aired earlier tonight.

01:24:31.760 --> 01:24:33.560
Pender will be transferred
back to prison

01:24:33.560 --> 01:24:34.800
In indiana in the morning.

01:24:34.800 --> 01:24:37.670
[♪]

01:24:45.310 --> 01:24:46.510
[sean]:
What was it like,

01:24:46.510 --> 01:24:48.480
Being the most wanted woman
in america?

01:24:48.480 --> 01:24:49.780
Horrible.

01:24:49.780 --> 01:24:51.110
You can't ever relax.

01:24:51.120 --> 01:24:53.320
The key is
moving forward,

01:24:53.320 --> 01:24:55.720
It's a waste of time
looking back.

01:24:55.720 --> 01:24:58.150
You did something,
you didn't do something,

01:24:58.160 --> 01:24:59.690
It doesn't really matter.

01:24:59.690 --> 01:25:03.830
Is what you do now,
today, tomorrow.

01:25:05.100 --> 01:25:06.860
You've got to have goals.

01:25:06.860 --> 01:25:08.560
A plan...

01:25:08.570 --> 01:25:10.770
You always got to have a plan.

01:25:10.770 --> 01:25:13.170
Is that why you started
dealing pot with rick?

01:25:13.170 --> 01:25:14.800
Rick was small-time.

01:25:14.810 --> 01:25:16.170
He hardly broke even.

01:25:16.170 --> 01:25:17.810
Drew was screwing him over,

01:25:17.810 --> 01:25:21.810
So I... I got the idea
that we should branch out.

01:25:21.810 --> 01:25:23.550
Took him up to purdue,

01:25:23.550 --> 01:25:27.680
And that was pretty much
the last normal day of my life.

01:25:29.150 --> 01:25:30.350
I never hurt anyone.

01:25:30.350 --> 01:25:33.420
I'm a good person.

01:25:40.900 --> 01:25:43.200
What are you doing?

01:25:43.200 --> 01:25:46.640
You paint
a pretty picture, sarah.

01:25:46.640 --> 01:25:48.870
Sweet girl,
wrong place, wrong time,

01:25:48.870 --> 01:25:53.340
But a lot of those other people,
they paint a much darker one--

01:25:53.340 --> 01:25:55.280
Extortion, coercion,
manipulation, murder.

01:25:55.280 --> 01:25:56.450
I'm not a murderer.

01:25:56.450 --> 01:25:58.280
Tell me the truth
about that night.

01:25:58.280 --> 01:26:00.550
It's not gonna change
your situation.

01:26:00.550 --> 01:26:01.880
You really think I would've
planned to kill them

01:26:01.890 --> 01:26:04.920
In my house with a shotgun
I bought the day before?

01:26:04.920 --> 01:26:07.190
Maybe.

01:26:07.190 --> 01:26:09.320
Maybe you planned
to make it look

01:26:09.330 --> 01:26:11.260
Like rick's idea
all along.

01:26:11.260 --> 01:26:12.530
[shots echoing]

01:26:12.530 --> 01:26:14.830
[sobbing, crashing]

01:26:14.830 --> 01:26:16.330
[gasps deeply]

01:26:16.330 --> 01:26:18.630
[wailful sobbing]

01:26:21.400 --> 01:26:22.700
[sobs]:
She's still alive!

01:26:22.710 --> 01:26:24.540
Who would the cops believe?

01:26:24.540 --> 01:26:30.210
A petty criminal
or a pretty physics major?

01:26:30.210 --> 01:26:32.880
[sobbing and whimpering]

01:26:37.820 --> 01:26:38.950
[shot echoes]

01:26:42.330 --> 01:26:44.730
"when it comes to survival,

01:26:44.730 --> 01:26:48.360
I think sarah is capable
of doing anything."

01:26:48.370 --> 01:26:50.630
That's a quote
from your father.

01:26:53.200 --> 01:26:54.440
All I know is

01:26:54.440 --> 01:26:56.310
That you will
say, or do, anything

01:26:56.310 --> 01:26:57.510
To get what you want.

01:27:01.840 --> 01:27:03.780
[engine starts]

01:27:05.880 --> 01:27:08.820
You know something,
marshal harlan?

01:27:10.620 --> 01:27:14.360
You're a lot more handsome
in person than you are on tv.

01:27:14.360 --> 01:27:17.590
You must work out a lot.
